12	A Maiden	4		\nWhen I found your face on a pillow of leaves\r you had already erased it. A nest so heavy\r can stay in the heavens only by reversal.\r  \r By this law the knees are laced with abandon.\r  \r I said to the young man.\r  \r If watching is the manufacturer, and I lose you\r what angel takes the place of a dowry\r or distance in this leaf action?\r  \r  \r  \r  Subject to like passions as we are\r my soul herself, myself\r a possession I could not\r mistake for the man\r (his language and Latin)\r yet we are “taken to”\r a love passage\r I had hardly noticed\r in the late talk of money\r The work of love and the work of art\r has no sleeping part\r Is a drop of light\r in a small silver socket,\r a rosy dime\r in a daylight tryst\r Is a keeper and no spender\r As seeing who is invisible:\r a kind of flaxen thing\r caught in stone\r I obeyed and read further\r “I am hemmed”\r Though my heart were a pear tree\r threaded with fire\r Lion you leapt through me\r like fineness in the boundary gene\r  \r  \r  \r  \r Conductor you knit me\r as isthmus     Can I touch it\r Night is going 200 miles an hr\r as usual     In this way we find\r we are suddenly altered\r If I were a day would you\r like me better     Where were you\r you who in a bath changed meHow to be walking\r is a glorious porthole\r Must I insist on an absence\r more foolish and secret\r When your timber’s a forest\r I can’t see for the tree in my bed\r Gentle captive, it is\r a larger than murder\r we tender     Fond and afire\r my style and my anchor\r Master there’s a boat for no\r lesser completion than\r beauty’s sweetest dress\r when you look on me kind\r Who am I to stop this flowing\r Least of all that home mile\r Sinking in the real\r I dreamed there was a further island\r Perhaps (how I thought you)\r to salt that harness with pleasure\r  \r  \r  \r  \r Lovely hero where the lovely hero bounds\r an acre hidden between eros and its errors\r Finding a dozen darts beneath the skin of\r Watching the wire of a skinny flame\r No other lovely hero found the back\r behind her secret form of symmetry\r Her gleaming difference\r Her schoolish way in pretty understandings\r Said   Not done   Not said   Undone\r Wealthy sadness has a way of winning everyone\r This is the end of my body as you know it\r its superfluous penchant for love\r its poorer costume, its shiny disaster\r  \r  \r  \r  \r What is a maiden,\r                          boatswain,\r but a fiery lair\r and a teary citadel\r By the smallest shipwreck\r a daughter is laughter\r Yet equaled\r                          as in a fable\r this Gibraltar goes headlong\r in a just king’s love\r See how his hands\r are her mercy\r and measure\r her number and rescue\r O Perseus\r     Pythagoras\r     Pierre\r my Pierre\r  \r  \r  \r  \r What rules a body’s buried factions\r when laundered by morning\r  \r When called by our names\r although we are invisible\r  \r Sleeping I forget my animal\r When the animal comes\r I’m forgotten because of it\r  \r How was it called\r in its own country\r  \r crossing a street\r in order to come inside\r  \n	'200':201 'abandon':38 'absenc':248 'acr':350 'action':67 'afir':281 'alreadi':15 'alter':215 'although':502 'anchor':286 'angel':55 'anim':510,513 'art':118 'back':378 'bath':233 'beauti':297 'bed':268 'behind':379 'beneath':361 'better':225 'boat':291 'boatswain':434 'bodi':414,489 'bound':348 'boundari':186 'buri':491 'call':498,524 'captiv':270 'caught':156 'chang':234 'citadel':442 'come':514,535 'complet':295 'conductor':188 'costum':426 'could':82 'countri':528 'cross':529 'dart':360 'daughter':448 'day':220 'daylight':138 'differ':387 'dime':135 'disast':429 'distanc':63 'done':396 'dowri':61 'dozen':359 'dream':325 'dress':300 'drop':125 'end':411 'equal':452 'eras':16 'ero':353 'error':356 'everyon':407 'fabl':456 'face':7 'faction':492 'fieri':437 'find':211,357 'fine':183 'fire':176 'flame':371 'flaxen':154 'flow':313 'fond':279 'foolish':250 'forest':