37	Mind Core	12		\nIt considers those men that ambled &\r Flushed their swords & cut off the neck\r Of the blue horses & scraped off death\r Dust from the carcass — rape of women\r Tresses in boilers — the tin-colored animals\r On the viridian grasses in particular the\r Howler Monkey let the word shoot up\r To the spheres — later we charged our\r Blood with these accounts we hid the arms\r Unforgiving texts & designs sewn into\r Our tiny alabaster lockets. We visited\r The last ridge where Victor Jara\r Denounced the paramilitary — from\r La Obrera in the heights of  Tijuana we\r Sketched the reddish moon & scratched\r Poems those things that could carry\r The letters we hauled on our backs.\r We were separated from something we\r Could not describe yet we were in\r The totality in the long winding turquoise\r That broke us & put us back together\r Again. What was that totality? It could\r Not be written — Green moon, green blood — \r We wrote. We marched to the ends of\r Lacanjá Chansayab & the heights\r Of El Colorín Central México. We were too\r Late — the waters in which people bathed\r Were cloudy & malignant — bellies\r Bloated children leaned on the twig\r House women stood up some sat cross-\r Legged under the fire rays of noon — \r We knew they knew the rubble land\r Was not theirs or ours it was stuffed into\r The cigarette packs of the Ladino\r Hacendados who kicked up their short\r Boots in the City of Bones below.\r With our faces in new faces we rolled\r Back to LA. Do you change it? Do you\r Leave it the same?\r Words — what are they?\r A new cognition was required — then\r With the ecstasy of the unleashed\r Other things pulled us apart. Other things\r Reassembled us.\r Now we are here.\n	'account':62 'alabast':74 'ambl':8 'anim':37 'apart':282 'arm':66 'back':113,139,249 'bath':181 'belli':185 'bloat':186 'blood':59,154 'blue':18 'boiler':32 'bone':239 'boot':234 'broke':135 'carcass':26 'carri':106 'central':170 'chang':254 'chansayab':164 'charg'