47	Speculations about “I”	20		\ni \r I didn’t choose the word — \r it came pouring out of my throat\r like the water inside a drowned man.\r I didn’t even push on my stomach.\r I just lay there, dead (like he told me)\r & “I” came out.\r (I’m sorry, Father.\r “I” wasn’t my fault.)\r  \r ii \r (How did “I” feel?)\r Felt almost alive\r when I’d get in, like the Trojan horse.\r I’d sit on the bench\r (I didn’t look out of the eyeholes\r so I wouldn’t see the carnage).\r  \r iii \r (Is “I” speaking another language?)\r I said, “I” is dangerous.\r But at the time I couldn’t tell\r which one of us was speaking.\r  \r iv \r (Why “I”?)\r “I” was the closest I could get to the\r one I loved (who I believe was\r smothered in her playpen).\r Perhaps she gave birth\r to “I” before she died.\r  \r v \r I deny “I,”\r & the closer\r I get, the more\r “I” keeps receding.\r  \r vi \r I found “I”\r in the bulrushes\r raised by a dirtiness\r beyond imagination.\r I loved “I” like a stinky bed.\r While I hid in a sentence\r with a bunch of other words.\r  \r vii \r (What is “I”?)\r A transmission through space?\r A dismemberment of the spirit?\r More like opening the chest &\r throwing the heart out with the gizzards.\r  \r viii \r (Translation)\r Years later “I” came back\r wanting to be known.\r Like the unspeakable\r name of God, I tried\r my 2 letters, leaving\r the “O” for breath,\r like in the Bible,\r missing.\r  \r ix \r I am not the “I”\r in my poems. “I”\r is the net I try to pull me in with.\r  \r x \r I try to talk\r with “I,” but “I” doesn’t trust\r me. “I” says I am\r slippery by nature.\r  \r xi \r I made “I” do\r what I wasn’t supposed to do,\r what I didn’t want to do — \r defend me,\r stand as an example,\r stand in for what I was hiding.\r I treated “I” as if\r “I” wasn’t human.\r  \r xii \r They say that what I write\r belongs to me, that it is my true\r experience. They think it validates\r my endurance.\r But why pretend?\r “I” is a kind of terminal survival.\r  \