49	The Happy	22		\nIn a room more chicken coop than room,\r I rent a fan that feels on my face like sound. Low traffic\r from San Fernando, named for a king who\r became a city, a valley, a saint.\r We are meant to repeat his name. Instead\r I say prickly pear, a cactus\r which spreads its many-paddled hands\r into the space around itself. No pears.\r I call Mom to ask what the latest austerity measures mean.\r Some ants on the wall make their way from one\r unseeable point to another; the banks have closed.\r I tell her to barter; barter what, she says.\r An acquaintance posts “Tourism:\r The Best Way to Be an Ally to Greece”\r as if in each tourist’s pleasure bloomed\r a charity. Mules clabber down the stone paths\r loaded with grapes to make next year’s\r wine, if the tourists come back\r next year, and we hope they will. I say we,\r but I’m closer to they. Living temporarily\r in a neighborhood named for the happy, who were\r who exactly?\r I grow a little stiff with, a little lean with, a little faint with, a little\r worn with seeming.\r I must need to conquer my mind.\r The roses dead because of drought\r because whoever lives here cares enough\r to let their roses die. I must\r need to conquer the notion\r anything needs conquering.\r Something in me can’t tell\r what belongs. The ants\r for whom anything is a street.\r What sounded like a gate opening\r was eucalyptus branches dragging themselves along the tin roof.\r A yellow butterfly that has no interest in me.\r I have no interest in kings.\n	'acquaint':106 'alli':115 'along':257 'anoth':91 'ant':79,239 'anyth':227,242 'around':63 'ask':71 'auster':75 'back':147 'bank':93 'barter':100,101 'becam':32 'belong':237 'best':110 'bloom':125 'branch':254 'butterfli':263 'cactus':52 'call':68 'care':213 'chariti':127 'chicken':7 'citi':34 'clabber':129 'close':95 'closer':161 'come':146 'conquer':200,224,229 'coop':8 'dead':205 'die':219 'drag':255 'drought':208 'enough':214 'eucalyptus':253 'exact':176 'face':