53	Propositions	26		\nAnyone who begins a sentence with, “In all honesty ... ”\r is about to tell a lie. Anyone who says, “This is how I feel”\r had better love form more than disclosure. Same for anyone\r who thinks he thinks well because he had a thought.\r If  you say, “You’re ugly” to an ugly person — no credit\r for honesty, which must always be a discovery, an act\r that qualifies as an achievement. If  you persist\r you’re just a cruel bastard, a pig without a mirror,\r somebody who hasn’t examined himself enough.\r A hesitation hints at an attempt to be honest, suggests\r a difficulty is present. A good sentence needs\r a clause or two, interruptions, set off  by commas,\r evidence of a slowing down, a rethinking.\r Before I asked my wife to marry me, I told her\r I’d never be fully honest. No one, she said,\r had ever said that to her. I was trying\r to be radically honest, I said, but in fact\r had another motive. A claim without a “but” in it\r is, at best, only half  true. In all honesty,\r I was asking in advance to be forgiven.\n	'achiev':71 'act':66 'advanc':189 'alway':61 'anoth':167 'anyon':2,17,34 'ask':129,187 'attempt':98 'bastard':80 'begin':4 'best':178 'better':26 'claim':170 'claus':112 'comma':119 'credit':56 'cruel':79 'd':139 'difficulti':104 'disclosur':31 'discoveri':64 'enough':92 'ever':149 'evid':120 'examin':90 'fact':165 'feel':24 'forgiven':192 'form':28 'fulli':142 'good':108 'half':180 'hasn':88 'hesit':94 'hint':95 'honest':101,143,160 'honesti':10,58,184 'interrupt':115 'lie':16 'love':27 'marri':133 'mirror':85 'motiv':168 'must':60 'need':110 'never':140 'one':145 'persist':74 'person':54 'pig':82 'present':106 'proposit':1 'qualifi':68 'radic':159 're':49,76 'rethink':126 'said':147,150,162 'say':19,47 'sentenc':6,109 'set':116 'slow':123 'somebodi':86 'suggest':102 'tell':14 'think':36,38 'thought':44 'told':136 'tri':156 'true':181 'two':114 'ugli':50,53 'well':39 'wife':131 'without':83,171
