65	Limitations	36		\nThe subtlest strain a great musician weaves,\r Cannot attain in rhythmic harmony\r To music in his soul. May it not be\r Celestial lyres send hints to him? He grieves\r That half the sweetness of the song, he leaves\r Unheard in the transition. Thus do we\r Yearn to translate the wondrous majesty\r Of some rare mood, when the rapt soul receives\r A vision exquisite. Yet who can match\r The sunset’s iridescent hues? Who sing\r The skylark’s ecstasy so seraph-fine?\r We struggle vainly, still we fain would catch\r Such rifts amid life’s shadows, for they bring\r Glimpses ineffable of things divine.\r  \n	'amid':94 'attain':10 'bring':100 'cannot':9 'catch':91 'celesti':23 'divin':105 'ecstasi':79 'exquisit':64 'fain':89 'fine':83 'glimps':101 'great':6 'griev':30 'half':32 'harmoni':13 'hint':26 'hue':73 'ineff':102 'iridesc':72 'leav':39 'life':95 'limit':1 'lyre':24 'majesti':52 'match':68 'may':19 'mood':56 'music':15 'musician':7 'rapt':59 'rare':55 'receiv':61 'rhythmic':12 'rift':93 'send':25 'seraph':82 'seraph-fin':81 'shadow':97 'sing':75 'skylark':77 'song':37 'soul':18,60 'still':87 'strain':4 'struggl':85 'subtlest':3 'sunset':70 'sweet':34 'thing':104 'thus':44 'transit':43 'translat':49 'unheard':40 'vain':86 'vision':63 'weav':8 'wondrous':51 'would':90 'yearn':47 'yet':65
