88	River of Milk	56		\nbear with me      it wasn’t long ago I was brainless\r lazily pulling fireflies into my teeth       chewing them\r into pure light       so much of me then was nothing\r I could have fit into a sugar cube      my body burned\r like a barnful of feathers        nothing was on fire\r but fire was on everything       the wild mustard\r the rotting porch chair         a box of birth records        eventually\r even scorched earth goes green       though beneath it\r the dead might still luxuriate in their rage     my ancestor\r was a dervish saint     said to control a thick river of dark milk\r under his town        his people believed\r he could have spared them a drought       they ripped him to pieces\r like eagles tearing apart a snake    immediately they were filled\r with remorse       instead of burying him        they buried a bag\r of goat bones and azalea      my hair still carries that scent\r my eyes      black milk and a snake’s flicking tongue\r does this confuse you       there are so many ways to be deceived\r a butcher’s thumb pressed into the scale       a strange blue dress\r in a bathtub    the slowly lengthening night      I apologize\r I never aimed at eloquence      I told my mother I wouldn’t live\r through the year       then waited for a disaster      sitting cheerfully\r on cinder blocks pulled from a drained pond      tossing\r peanuts to squirrels     this is not the story she tells     hers filled\r with happy myths       fizzy pistons and plummy ghosts\r it’s true I suppose       you grow to love the creatures you create\r some of them come out with pupils swirling       others with teeth\n	'ago':11 'aim':196 'ancestor':88 'apart':123 'apolog':193 'azalea':144 'bag':139 'barn':46 'bathtub':187 'bear':4 'believ':107 'beneath':77 'birth':68 'black':153 'block':219 'blue':183 'bodi':42 'bone':142 'box':66 'brainless':14 'buri':134,137 'burn':43 'butcher':174 'carri':148 'chair':64 'cheer':216 'chew':21 'cinder':218 'co