116	I Let Love In	71		\nWhen they were together she thought it God’s punishment.\r When he left she thought it God’s punishment.\r  \r When vermin overrun the city’s boardinghouses\r and highrises it’s God sticking a hose\r into the Devil’s hole to flood him out.\r  \r And when the floodwaters rose,\r where was everyone?\r  \r When fog risen from the lake assimilates varietals\r of exhaust, evolves through the financial district, renders toxic\r the neighbourhoods, swells over suburbs, the Devil\r has forsaken another project, saying sometimes\r I can’t fucking concentrate on anything.\r  \r He says he does what he does sometimes because\r the Devil gets in like water through his weak places.\r  \r When it rains like now the Devil yells at God\r I’ve told you not to call me that. When it rains like now.\r And every time God laughs at this\r  \r roofs lift off along the Eastern Seaboard. The Eastern Seaboard\r will never understand.\r  \r When we are broken, to whom are we opened?\r  \r God’s taken all the fish home to live with him, honey.\r  \r And when the earth shakes that’s God rearranging furniture\r not a bomb in the subway like we thought.\r  \r If you feel the Devil with you, he is there.\r If you think God has abandoned you,\r you are abandoned, his attention\r  \r on the World Series, more important than any one man,\r smiting the hell out of the Rangers’ big bats as the Giants\r lift fingers to the sky in praise and the ordnance\r deployed in his name, in making straight he way,\r would fill the oceans.\r  \r And each foreclosure is a failure of belief,\r each immortal jellyfish a failure of belief.\r  \r When those who will ruin us are elected,\r where is everyone?\r  \r And when I return from the desert it’s with the Devil\r cast out. With God cast out. Because it wasn’t really me\r  \r who did those things before, that wasn’t me.\n	'abandon':211,215 'along':146 'anoth':82 'anyth':92 'assimil':62 'attent':217 'bat':236 'belief':270,277 'big':235 'boardi