150	Summer    (a love poem)	77		\nI wanted to be sure this was our island\r so we could walk between the long stars by the sea\r though your hips are slight and caught in the air\r like a moth at the end of a river around my arms\r I am unable to understand the sun your dizzy spells\r when you form a hand around me on the sand\r I offer you my terrible sanity\r the eternal voice that keeps me from reaching you\r though we are close to each other every autumn\r I feel the desperation of a giant freezing in cement\r when I touch the door you're pressed against\r the color of your letter that reminds me of flamingos\r isn't that what you mean?\r the pleasure of hands and\r lips wetter than the ocean\r or the brilliant pain of\r breathless teeth in a\r turbulent dream on a roof\r while I thought of nothing\r else except you against\r the sky as I unfolded you\r like my very life a liquid\r signal of enormous love we\r invented like a comet that\r splits the air between us!\r the earth looks shiny wrapped in steam and ermine\r tired of us perspiring at every chance on the floor\r below I bring you an ash tray out of love for the\r ice palace because it is the end of summer the end\r of the sun because you are in season like a blue\r rug you are my favorite violin when you sit and \r peel my eyes with your great surfaces seem intimate\r when we merely touch the thread of life and kiss\r  \r 7.30.69\n	'7.30.69':268 'air':34,183 'arm':46 'around':44,62 'ash':210 'autumn':90 'blue':238 'breathless':141 'brilliant':138 'bring':207 'caught':31 'cement':100 'chanc':201 'close':85 'color':111 'comet':179 'could':16 'desper':94 'dizzi':55 'door':105 'dream':146 'earth':187 'els':155 'end':40,223,227 'enorm':173 'ermin':194 'etern':74 'everi':89,200 'except':156 'eye':251 'favorit':243 'feel':92 'flamingo':119 'floor':204 'form':59 'freez':98 'giant':97 'great':254 'hand':61,129 'hip':27 'ice':217 'intim':257 'invent':176 'island':13 'isn':120 'keep':77 'kiss':267 'letter':114 'li