163	The Untold Witch	80		\n1\r She would\r sigh, if she\r could think of\r anything intolerable.\r her numbers\r fold, in\r planes she can\r not describe.\r Does she\r close her eyes for\r that faint\r red of processes?\r Come to me,\r by instinct or\r for mathematics’\r sake.\r  \r  \r 2\r She\r moves\r in a metaphor of\r action.\r Heaven, she\r says, is\r hell\r remembered.\r Outside her\r gaze, I’m\r stranded\r on fraudulent heights.\r No\r tune I\r know is far\r enough out.\r  \r  \r 3\r Man is a matter of\r walking\r upright, but she\r suggests happiness.\r Her whole\r power\r is one the side\r of vagueness.\r Everything I\r need to\r know about her is\r just before me.\r What\r can I learn\r that is not already\r gone?\r  \r  \r 4\r Mountains rule\r the world because\r she’s\r from the hills.\r When she stands\r perpendicular to the\r sun’s rays, her\r light is confined.\r If she\r turns,\r the objective\r weakens.\r We shall not all\r rise, but\r all\r be modified.\r  \r  \r 5\r I see her\r long after\r she has\r gone away.\r There are whole\r systems\r she\r doesn’t respond to.\r If you\r look long enough\r everything\r is hydraulics.\r Out of a\r series of partial\r images, she is the\r one that detaches.\r  \r  \r 6\r If I could\r remember\r her, we\r might build.\r Will my\r words be fan-\r tastic enough to\r count?\r Whatever\r happens now, we\r have been\r opposite.\r Please believe me,\r I would\r seek you if I\r had the distance.\r  \r  \r 7\r Given\r time and\r invention, she\r will surface.\r She will\r scratch,\r meditate, and some\r story will suffer.\r I refuse to\r believe\r things unsupported necessarily\r fall.\r She deprives my\r dreams\r of un-\r reality.\r  \r  \r 8\r The hardest\r step to take is\r always the\r next.\r She is written\r across\r her\r face.\r We are\r what we\r are, momentary\r coincidence.\r She is\r body,\r speaking\r through body.\r  \r  \r 9\r She will claim, for\r instance, King\r Solomon planted\r baobabs in India.\r And it\r may\r be\r true.\r A fine long\r rain\r penetrates farther\r than storms.\r Food is\r necessary\r and\r  also logic.\r  \r  \r 10\r Sometimes I’m\r angry, and\r not at\r anything in particular.\r She has\r seven\r divisions, but\r no borders.\r I could\r change your name, since\r you always\r wanted to be fictional.\r Another\r unsolved\r dream, under\r the bridge\r  \r  \r 11\r She has, it would\r seem, no\r natural\r inclination to rise.\r She is\r whatever I\r cannot get\r rid of.\r She’s whatever\r refuses\r to be\r information.\r She is my\r absence,\r my only secure\r reference.\r  \r  \r 12\r Just when I’m\r ready to let\r go, satisfaction\r is satisfaction.\r Curious text, where\r we’re commanded to acquire\r Nirvana.\r Nothing but\r impatience\r could prompt our\r abrupt recognition.\r she says virginity\r of the mind\r can be\r restored.\r  \r  \r 13\r Let me\r not praise\r her past her\r due.\r She is\r a heap of\r pebbles\r in exquisite random.\r Her laughter\r rings\r empty, where there\r were crowds.\r My arms\r around\r you, my\r love, are phantoms.\r  \r  \r 14\r She appears sometimes\r to be talking\r about\r other data.\r It is as\r if she\r knew a separate\r category.\r I tell\r her, weeping’s\r no proof\r of the resurrection.\r All\r of her is\r curved\r and alters.\r  \r  \r 15\r She can\r only\r be pictured\r as catastrophe.\r She con-\r fuses\r concepts with\r irony.\r Her thought spreads,\r like\r children\r running home.\r She\r finds comfort in\r the most outrageous\r limbs.\r  \r  \r 16\r The moon, according\r to her, is\r a symbol\r for shine.\r Residues\r provide the\r passion\r of thought.\r Her reflexes\r condition\r my\r mythology.\r She is the\r energy\r of my\r indexes.\r  \r  \r 17\r When she\r snarls at\r me, my\r senses sharpen.\r Who could expect\r her,\r without\r lying?\r She is a\r color\r outside\r the octave.\r Her rituals\r divide my\r life\r from its labors.\r  \r  \r 18\r She makes\r the right\r answer\r sound foolish.\r The righteous\r glory\r in their un-\r certainty.\r Two\r nuts represent\r us in\r divination.\r The only\r thing she\r comes home in\r is twilight.\r  \r  \r 19\r She sits\r in the\r street, making\r detours.\r Her history is\r rich\r in in-\r decisions.\r She is\r present,\r inclusive,\r untransformed.\r I do not\r pretend\r to know\r how the flood came.\r  \r  \r 20\r A hymn\r describes the\r monotony\r of her expectations.\r She was\r created\r from the sweat\r of peacocks.\r Children\r defend themselves\r with shame\r and experience.\r All her\r objects\r answer to the\r same name.\r  \r  \r 21\r Better a blank\r wall than\r simple\r dark.\r The play in\r her muscle de-\r termines\r where my eyes focus.\r She\r sleeps at\r the curve\r of my spine.\r She wouldn’t\r believe\r me, if I\r were to tell her.\n	'1':4 '10':324 '11':360 '12':394 '13':432 '14':466 '15':502 '16':531 '17':560 '18':590 '19':620 '2':44 '20':650 '21':682 '3':75 '4':116 '5':155 '6':195 '7':232 '8':264 '9':293 'abrupt':421 'absenc':389 'accord':534 'acquir':413 'across':277 'action':51 'alreadi':114 'also':322 'alter':501 'alway':271,349 'angri':328 'anoth':354 'answer':595,677 'anyth':13,332 'appear':468 'arm':459 'around':460 'away':164 'baobab':302 'believ':221,252,712 'better':683 'blank':685 'bodi':289,292 'border':341 'bridg':359 'build':203 'came':649 'cannot':375 'catastroph':509 'categori':484 'certainti':604 'chang':344 'children':520,667 'claim':296 'close':26 'coincid':286 'color':578 'come':35,615 'comfort':525 'command':411 'con':511 'concept':513 'condit':550 'confin':139 'could':10,198,343,418,570 'count':212 'creat':661 'crowd':457 'curious':406 'curv':499,705 'dark':689 'data':475 'de':695 'decis':634 'defend':668 'depriv':258 'describ':23,653 'detach':194 'detour':627 'distanc':231 'divid':584 'divin':610 'divis':338 'doesn':170 'dream':260,356 'due':440 'empti':453 'energi':556 'enough':73,178,210 'everyth':96,179 'expect':571,658 'experi':673 'exquisit':448 'eye':