196	Dothead	99		\nWell yes, I said, my mother wears a dot.\r I know they said "third eye" in class, but it's not\r an eye eye, not like that. It's not some freak\r third eye that opens on your forehead like\r on some Chernobyl baby. What it means\r is, what it's showing is, there's this unseen\r eye, on the inside. And she's marking it.\r It's how the X that says where treasure's at\r is not the treasure, but as good as treasure.—\r All right. What I said wasn't half so measured.\r In fact, I didn't say a thing. Their laughter\r had made my mouth go dry. Lunch was after\r World History; that week was India—myths,\r caste system, suttee, all the Greatest Hits.\r The white kids I was sitting with were friends,\r at least as I defined a friend back then.\r So wait, said Nick, does your mom wear a dot?\r I nodded, and I caught a smirk on Todd—\r She wear it to the shower? And to bed?—\r whie Jesse sucked his chocolate milk and Brad\r was getting ready for another stab.\r I said, Hand me that ketchup packet there.\r And Nick said, What? I snatched it, twitched the tear,\r and squeezed a dollop on my thumb and worked\r circles till the red planet entered the house of war\r and on my forehead for the world to see\r my third eye burned those schoolboys in their seats,\r their flesh in little puddles underneath,\r pale pools where Nataraja cooled his feet.	'anoth':189 'babi':45 'back':147 'bed':176 'brad':184 'burn':240 'cast':124 'caught':163 'chernobyl':44 'chocol':181 'circl':218 'class':18 'cool':256 'defin':144 'didn':101 'dollop':212 'dot':10,158 'dothead':1 'dri':113 'enter':223 'eye':16,24,25,35,59,239 'fact':99 'feet':258 'flesh':247 'forehead':40,231 'freak':33 'friend':139,146 'get':186 'go':112 'good':85 'greatest':129 'half':95 'hand':193 'histori':118 'hit':130 'hous':225 'india':122 'insid':62 'jess':178 'ketchup':196 'kid':133 'know':12 'laughter':107 'least':141 'like':27,41 'littl':249 'lunch':114 'made':109 'mark':66 'mean':48 'measur':97 'milk':182 'mom':