203	Night Song for Missy	101		\nMy bones tied up with his bones at night,\r him falling asleep in my arm after wrasslin me,\r calling it love in some kind of low whisper\r no dog would believe. I know his every smell,\r every way the littlest corner of him be stinkin\r underneath me, on top of me, while our children\r snore in the corner, then he creep out the way\r he creep in, before the cock crow at the sun.\r In daylight he act like we strangers, on the edge\r of the field, his little tan children of mine turning\r brown, playing more than working cause they his\r children, Missy look over at me while I look \r over at her, both of us got some kind of papers\r on this same man that say he own both of us,\r the man who owes us even we he die cause\r the Bible say you gotta look after the widow.\r But when he die it will be cause Missy and me\r locked eyes many days and hated him like one\r wronged woman made out of two, him standing\r up there on the porch studyin everything—\r his eyes lit up like he the Lord of all creation.\r hush now, night wind on my skin, hush now\r bird lost in trees, hush now, hungry moon\r  \n	'act':82 'arm':19 'asleep':16 'believ':35 'bibl':149 'bird':212 'bone':6,11 'brown':99 'call':23 'caus':104,147,164 'children':58,95,107 'cock':74 'corner':45,62 'creation':202 'creep':65,70 'crow':75 'day':171 'daylight':80 'die':146,160 'dog':33 'edg':88 'even':143 'everi':39,41 'everyth':191 'eye':169,193 'fall':15 'field':91 'got':122 'gotta':152 'hate':173 'hungri':218 'hush':203,210,216 'kind':28,124 'know':37 'like':83,175,196 'lit':194 'littl':93 'littlest':44 'lock':168 'look':109,115,153 'lord':199 'lost':213 'love':25 'low':30 'made':179 'man':130,139 'mani':170 'mine':97 'missi':4,108,165 'moon':219 'night':1,13,205 'one':176 'owe':141 'paper':126 'play':100 'porch':189 'say':132,150 'skin':209 'smell':40 'snore':59 'song':2 'stand':184 'stinkin':49 'stranger':85 'studyin':190 'sun':78 'tan':94 'tie':7 'top':53 'tree':215 'turn':98 'two