228	Safe	108		\nYou used to be able to flag a ride in this country.  Impossible now—everyone is afraid    of strangers.   Well, there was fear then too,  and it was mutual: drivers versus hitchhikers.  And we rode without seat belts,  insurance or beliefs.  People  would see me far ahead on a hill like a seedling,  watch me grow in the windshield  and not know they were going to stop until  they got right up to me.  Maybe they wanted  company or thought I’d give them  some excitement.  It was the age  of impulse, of lonesome knee jerks.  An old woman  stopped, blew smoke in my face  and after I was already in her car she asked me  if I wanted a ride.  I’m telling you.  Late one night a construction boss pulled over.  One of his crew had been hit  by the mob, he said as he drove, distraught  and needing to talk to someone.  We rode around for a long time.  He said, I never wore a gun to a funeral before,  but they’ve gotta be after me too.  Then he looked at me and patted the bulge  in his coat.  Don’t worry, he said, you’re safe.\n	'abl':6 'afraid':18 'age':91 'ahead':48 'alreadi':111 'around':159 'ask':116 'belief':42 'belt':39 'blew':102 'boss':132 'bulg':191 'car':114 'coat':194 'compani':79 'construct':131 'countri':13 'crew':138 'd':83 'distraught':150 'driver':31 'drove':149 'everyon':16 'excit':87 'face':106 'far':47 'fear':24 'flag':8 'funer':173 'give':84 'go':66 'got':71 'gotta':178 'grow':57 'gun':170 'hill':51 'hit':141 'hitchhik':33 'imposs':14 'impuls':93 'insur':40 'jerk':97 'knee':96 'know':63 'late':127 'like':52 'lonesom':95 'long':162 'look':185 'm':124 'mayb':76 'mob':144 'mutual':30 'need':152 'never':167 'night':129 'old':99 'one':128,135 'pat':189 'peopl':43 'pull':133 're':201 'ride':10,122 'right':72 'rode':36,158 'safe':1,202 'said':146,165,199 'seat':38 'see':45 'seedl':54 'smoke':103 'someon':156 'stop':68,101 'stranger':20 'talk':154 'tell':125 'thought':81 'time':163 'use':3 've':177 'versus':32 'want':78,120 'watch':55 'well':21 'winds