237	Nights on Planet Earth	111		\n1\rGravel paths on hillsides amid moon-drawn vineyards,\rclick of pearls upon a polished nightstand \rsoft as rainwater, self-minded stars, oboe music \rdistant as the grinding of icebergs against the hull\rof the self and the soul in the darkness \rchanting to the ecstatic chance of existence.\rDeep is the water and long is the moonlight \rinscribing addresses in quicksilver ink,\rbuilding the staircase a lover forever pauses upon.\rDeep is the darkness and long is the night,\rsolid the water and liquid the light. How strange \rthat they arrive at all, nights on planet earth. \r2\rSometimes, not often but repeatedly, the past invades my dreams in the form of a familiar neighborhood I can no longer locate, \ra warren of streets lined with dark cafés and unforgettable bars, a place where I can sing by heart every song on every jukebox,\ra city that feels the way the skin of an octopus looks pulse-changing from color to color, laminar and fluid and electric,\ra city of shadow-draped churches, of busses on dim avenues, or riverlights, or canyonlands, but always a city, and wonderful, and lost.\rSometimes it resembles Amsterdam, students from the ballet school like fanciful gazelles shooting pool in pink tights and soft, shapeless sweaters,\ror Madrid at 4AM, arguing the 18th Brumaire with angry Marxists, or Manhattan when the snowfall crowns every trash-can king of its Bowery stoop,\ror Chicago, or Dublin, or some ideal city of the imagination, as in a movie you can neither remember entirely nor completely forget, \rbarracuda-faced men drinking sake like yakuza in a Harukami novel, women sipping champagne or arrack, the rattle of beaded curtains in the back,\rthe necklaces of Christmas lights reflected in raindrops on windows, the taste of peanuts and their shells crushed to powder underfoot, \ralways real, always elusive, always a city, and wonderful, and lost. All night I wander alone, searching in vain for the irretrievable.\r3\rIn the night I will drink from a cup of ashes and yellow paint.\rIn the night I will gossip with the clouds and grow strong.\rIn the night I will cross rooftops to watch the sea tremble in a dream.\rIn the night I will assemble my army of golden carpenter ants.\rIn the night I will walk the towpath among satellites and cosmic dust.\rIn the night I will cry to the roots of potted plants in empty offices.\rIn the night I will gather the feathers of pigeons in a honey jar.\rIn the night I will become an infant before your flag.\n	'1':5 '18th':227 '2':105 '3':338 '4am':224 'address':66 'alon':331 'alway':193,316,318,320 'amid':10 'among':400 'amsterdam':203 'angri':230 'ant':391 'argu':225 'armi':387 'arrack':286 'arriv':98 'ash':349 'assembl':385 'avenu':187 'back':294 'ballet':207 'bar':138 'barracuda':271 'barracuda-fac':270 'bead':290 'becom':439 'boweri':245 'brumair':228 'build':70 'buss':184 'café':135 'canyonland':191 'carpent':390 'champagn':284 'chanc':53 'chang':166 'chant':49 'chicago':248 'christma':298 'church':182 'citi':153,177,195,254,322 'click':15 'cloud':361 'color':168,170 'complet':268 'cosmic':403 'cri':410 'cross':370 'crown':237 'crush':312 'cup':347 'curtain':291 'dark':48,81,134 'deep':56,78 'dim':186 'distant':31 'drape':181 'drawn':13 'dream':115,379 'drink':274,344 'dublin':250 'dust':404 'earth':4,104 'ecstat':52 'electr':175 'elus':319 'empti':418 'entir':266 'everi':147,150,238 'exist':55 'face':272 'familiar':121 'fanci':210 'feather':427 'feel':155 'flag':444 'fluid':173 'forev':75 'forget':269 'form':118 'gather':425 'gazell':211 'golden':389 'gossip':358 'gravel':6 'grind':34 'grow':363 'harukami':280 'heart':146 'hillsid':9 'honey':432 'hull':39 'iceberg':36 'ideal':253 'imagin':257 'infant':441 'ink':69 'inscrib':65 'invad':113 'irretriev':337 'jar':433 'jukebox':151 'king':242 'laminar':171 'light':93,299 'like':209,276 'line':132 'liquid':91 'locat':127 'long':61,83 'longer':126 'look':163 'lost':199,326 'lover':74 'madrid':222 'man