307	Weighing Light	144		\nOften the slightest gesture is most telling,As when he reaches tenderly in passing To pluck the yellow leaf from the dark fall Of her hair, or even the absence of all gesture: The way she doesn’t need to turn to know Who, in this gathering of friends, has touched her. It was as if he dreamed some private garden. Perhaps he woke from it, mid-reach, to find His hand too near her hair in this crowded yard, And maybe even now she’s shuttering in (She’s even better than you or I at that) A storm of worry and recrimination— Did anyone notice? how could he do that here!— By seamlessly continuing to tell you About her trip to see her favorite Vermeer This morning in the Delft show at the Met: “So now they say she isn’t weighing pearls Or gold or anything—it’s just the light Gleaming off empty scales.” So much is hard To know for sure. If I confronted her, She’d say it was just a leaf—who could afford To disagree? Could we? Now she’s explaining How the girl faces a mirror we can’t see into And how behind her hangs a gloomy painting Of the Last Judgment: “Over her head God Floats in a cloud,” she says, “like a thought balloon.”   But you don’t hear. You’re watching me. I nod.\n	'absenc':32 'afford':184 'anyon':109 'anyth':152 'balloon':229 'behind':206 'better':95 'cloud':223 'confront':172 'continu':119 'could':112,183,187 'crowd':82 'd':175 'dark':24 'delft':135 'disagre':186 'doesn':39 'dream':60 'empti':160 'even':30,86,94 'explain':192 'face':196 'fall':25 'favorit':129 'find':73 'float':220 'friend':51 'garden':63 'gather':49 'gestur':6,35 'girl':195 'gleam':158 'gloomi':210 'god':219 'gold':150 'hair':28,79 'hand':75 'hang':208 'hard':165 'head':218 'hear':234 'isn':145 'judgment':215 'know':45,167 'last':214 'leaf':21,181 'light':2,157 'like':226 'mayb':85 'met':139 'mid':70 'mid-reach':69 'mirror':198 'morn':132 'much':163 'near':77 'need':41 'nod':240 'notic':110 'often':3 'paint':211 'pass':16 'pearl':148 'perhap':64 'pluck':18 'privat':62