316	Shock Lessons, a Paddock Scripture	150		\nexploring the farm as a child I would part the tall grasses,\r moving through the dirt beneath the thick rushes.\r consisting mainly of overgrown clover and clusters of foliage,\r I’d map the distance that made up our property. it seemed endless,\r that innocent drive to run further beneath the ceiling of leaves,\r expanses of earth shifting beneath a child’s slight weight.\r I would imagine how far the landscape stretched.\r one afternoon when my parents were at the races\r I followed the pasture floor to the fenceline at the back of the property.\r wanting to go further, I hovered a blade of grass over the ticking wire\r as I had watched Dad do so many times, to test if it was safe to cross.\r feeling nothing, I wrapped my hands around one of the copper threads —\r struck by that first surge through the body, electricity\r running like a vein of blood beneath the skin\r as though a voice screamed through a haze, blinding my eyes\r and rattling my mind with panic.\r no longer wishing to know more, to understand,\r I stood startled at the trapped earth and wires\r that had run a painful electric current through my body.\r it would have been foolish to even attempt climbing\r over into the neighboring paddock.\r all I could do then was give up.\n	'afternoon':78 'around':137 'attempt':212 'back':96 'beneath':22,54,63,158 'blade':107 'blind':169 'blood':157 'bodi':150,204 'ceil':56 'child':11,65 'climb':213 'clover':30 'cluster':32 'consist':26 'copper':141 'could':221 'cross':130 'current':201 'd':36 'dad':118 'dirt':21 'distanc':39 'drive':50 'earth':61,192 'electr':151,200 'endless':47 'even':211 'expans':59 'explor':6 'eye':171 'far':73 'farm':8 'feel':131 'fencelin':93 'first':146 'floor':90 'foliag':34 'follow':87 'foolish':209 'give':225 'go':102 'grass':17,109 'hand':136 'haze':168 'hover':105 'imagin':71 'innoc':49 'know':182 'landscap':75 'leav':58 'lesson':2 'like':153 'longer':179 'made':41 'main':27 'mani':121 