338	Rosalind’s Madrigal	165		\nLove in my bosom like a bee\r   Doth suck his sweet;\rNow with his wings he plays with me,\r   Now with his feet.\rWithin mine eyes he makes his nest,\rHis bed amidst my tender breast;\rMy kisses are his daily feast,\rAnd yet he robs me of my rest.\r   Ah, wanton, will ye?\rAnd if I sleep, then percheth he\r   With pretty flight,\rAnd makes his pillow of my knee\r   The livelong night.\rStrike I my lute, he tunes the string;\rHe music plays if so I sing;\rHe lends me every lovely thing;\rYet cruel he my heart doth sting.\r   Whist, wanton, still ye!\rElse I with roses every day\r   Will whip you hence,\rAnd bind you, when you long to play,\r   For your offense.\rI’ll shut mine eyes to keep you in,\rI’ll make you fast it for your sin,\rI’ll count your power not worth a pin.\rAlas! what hereby shall I win\r   If he gainsay me?\rWhat if I beat the wanton boy\r   With many a rod?\rHe will repay me with annoy,\r   Because a god.\rThen sit thou safely on my knee,\rAnd let thy bower my bosom be;\rLurk in mine eyes, I like of thee.\rO Cupid, so thou pity me,\r   Spare not, but play thee!\n	'ah':54 'ala':158 'amidst':36 'annoy':184 'beat':171 'bed':35 'bee':10 'bind':121 'bosom':7,200 'bower':198 'boy':174 'breast':39 'count':151 'cruel':100 'cupid':211 'daili':44 'day':115 'doth':11,104 'els':110 'everi':96,114 'eye':29,135,205 'fast':144 'feast':45 'feet':26 'flight':67 'gainsay':166 'god':187 'heart':103 'henc':119 'herebi':160 'keep':137 'kiss':41 'knee':74,194 'lend':94 'let':196 'like':8,207 'livelong':76 'll':132,141,150 'long':125 'love':4,97 'lurk':202 'lute':81 'madrig':3 'make':31,69,142 'mani':176 'mine':28,134,204 'music':87 'nest':33 'night':77 'o':210 'offens':130 'percheth':63 'pillow':71 'pin':157 'piti':214 'play':20,88,127,219 'power':153 'pretti':66 'repay':181 'rest':53 'rob':49 'rod':178 'rosalind':1 'rose':113 'safe':191 'shall':161 'shut':133 'sin':148 'sing':92 'sit':189 'sleep':61 'spare':216 'still':108 'sting':105 's