416	Platonic Love	183		\n1\r  Indeed I must confess,\r  When souls mix ’tis an happiness,\rBut not complete till bodies too do join,\rAnd both our wholes into one whole combine;\rBut half of heaven the souls in glory taste\r  Till by love in heaven at last \r  Their bodies too are placed.\r                   2\r  In thy immortal part\r  Man, as well as I, thou art.\rBut something ’tis that differs thee and me,\rAnd we must one even in that difference be.\rI thee both as a man and woman prize,\r  For a perfect love implies\r  Love in all capacities.\r                   3\r  Can that for true love pass\r  When a fair woman courts her glass?\rSomething unlike must in love’s likeness be:\rHis wonder is one and variety.\rFor he whose soul nought but a soul can move\r  Does a new Narcissus prove,\r  And his own image love.\r                   4\r  That souls do beauty know\r  ’Tis to the body’s help they owe;\rIf when they know’t they straight abuse that trust\rAnd shut the body from’t, ’tis as unjust\rAs if I brought my dearest friend to see\r  My mistress and at th’instant he\r  Should steal her quite from me.\n	'1':3 '2':51 '3':98 '4':146 'abus':167 'art':62 'beauti':150 'bodi':18,47,155,173 'brought':182 'capac':97 'combin':29 'complet':16 'confess':7 'court':109 'dearest':184 'differ':67,78 'even':75 'fair':107 'friend':185 'glass':111 'glori':37 'half':31 'happi':13 'heaven':33,43 'help':157 'imag':144 'immort':54 'impli':93 'inde':4 'instant':193 'join':21 'know':151,163 'last':45 'like':118 'love':2,41,92,94,103,116,145 'man':56,85 'mistress':189 'mix':10 'move':135 'must':6,73,114 'narcissus':139 'new':138 'nought':130 'one':27,74,123 'owe':159 'part':55 'pass':104 'perfect':91 'place':50 'platon':1 'prize':88 'prove':140 'quit':198 'see':187 'shut':171 'someth':64,112 'soul':9,35,129,133,148 'steal':196 'straight':166 'tast':38 'th':192 'thee':68,81 'thi':53 'thou':61 'till':17,39 'tis':11,65,152,176 'true':102 'trust':169 'unjust':178 'unlik':113 'varieti':125 