450	A Twenty-fourth Poem about Horses	107		\nSteed out of my dusk and a dusk, now, for the species,\rveins deltawise down your silky inner thigh,\rveins trickling from one eye down the roan cliffside\rof a nose vaulted and chanceled for winds of the Pleistocene,\ryou have come, you paw patiently, that is the main thing,\rthe fields between stretch wider and we, the restless, are everywhere\rsave where your nostril quivers, arches, and you snort in the night.\rWe who debouch into all places dream of you now nowhere.\rYou come to a woman’s hand: that smile. You come to a\rchild’s hand, giggling and shivers. Your hot breath pleasures soldiers.\rHarnessed to caisson with bannered coffin, to the barouche\rat a state wedding, you are ambassador from the eldest  kingdom.\rThe King of Brazil sent a forest of teak to pave the streets\rgirdling the Pantheon, to muffle the clatter you hauled there.\rWhen we spurred you against Wellington’s infantry squares,\ryou side-ran them or reared back. The god of catasrophes took note.\rSad banner you were in the prophecies of Sweet Medicine,\rthe whiskered whitneys bringing and spawning your manes and tails\ramong the Arapaho, Cheyenne, Lakota, Kiowa,\ryour speed between their loins a drumming into decline.\rUnder Tutankhamun, the generalissimo who rode you hummed\rhis tenth title: Overseer of Works in the Hill of Gritstone,\rwhile there in those Works among the pulling men pulled also\ryour brother, sent down because of a freakish temperament.\rMuir knew you on both shores, and van der Post knew you,\rmufti lords recognizing a lord in service. Nuzzle them both.\rThey say that Poseidon at Onchestos, breaking you as a colt,\rhad your driver leap off where the road entered forest,\rand watched to see what you’d do, the rig rattling--smash it\ragainst the trunks on the run, or walk it through tall shadows.\rWhere you linger for shade on the veldt, branches level,\ra tree is the only tree. Your water, the only water.\rFlickers of hair along your neck’s crest release\rthe only signal. Which staggers from storm cloud to browse oats.\rStubby melted candle, your recessed phallus makes\rno howitzer but glistens a coat whose sheen ripples off.\rFor I imagine that Li Ho, seeing good men misused\ras you were, foresaw your withdrawal from our night grasses.\rFor your standing here re-ordains neither Akhilleus\rnor Cuchulain. Dew braids your mane with fresh constellations.\rFor what shall we make of you, made into goddess, mare\rsacrificed but receiving cult also among the footloose\ron the steppes: mother ridden by god-spear, great mam thus\rcaptured, cinched, spurred? though your flanks shudder unfettered.\rThrough mists we flash bits of mirror, but from them\ryou pound abreast, neither parent, eyes orbing the two sides.\rFor that demigod’s eye, tiding, capsizes anyone\rwho would turn trainer. And this one goes on into the bond.\rA trainer aims at one thing, but what tingles him is force\rhinting at the uncontainable, the opponent.\rAnd the top tamers, spook-soothers, the whisperers,\rwill write their books but miss the appointment. It is not inscribed.\rThe two  grooms beside you in Hokusai’s whitewater cascade\rlave you with splashes of it, currying your bulk,\rhoisting your nosebag--and no one has set the timer, everywhere\rit is one sound, stampede steadied and rocking in it.\rYour great-grandparents, unicorn wild asses\rfrom Persia and Scythia, fostered childbirth but also pissed plagues,\rthe unharnessable summum totium browsing in ocean,\ran eye-spangled three-legged mountain. Hell and cloud in your seed!\rIt was your miniature stature at the beginning, Maria Tallchief\rat ten, that wedged you between giants into the straightaway.\rAnd the reindeer modeled from smudge in the Font de Gaume grotto\rat Les Eyzies, fading across your body, trails a third antler\rlike a skater’s scarf through your head, broadening out,\ra dancer’s arm rippling after the total gather.\rLooking back from the pass at his mounted escorts, flashing them\rthree turns back down the corkscrew, the Fourteenth Dalai Lama\rsaw them slumped on your back, the red of Rahu in splashes\rand trickling stillness. And dripping you still awaited their nudges.\rIn that patience, the kernel of the twister moan-lifting\rover Kansas, the shrapnel clatter of your take-off.\rAcross that aftermath, bubbling through wind-sound or the mind’s\rrise from its cringe, the flubber-flutter of moody-moodlessness.\rSo the unforeseen from you opposes the blindly seen in us--\ryour fuse as a spurter, jump-taker, yet a curb also\rto our unsnaffled berserkness.  For the berserking Greek says\rthat only that ass’s horn or hoof, cut off and cupped upward,\rcan hold any of the cold torrent under the world,\rimplacable Styx, All else, graces or muons, it crumbles.\rAnd every jot which that flow dissolves, the images\rwith their assessors, has rolled in us. And you have stood\rcalmly beside us, your shot breath a bloom in the cold,\ryour hooves hammers yet also the last and only chalice.\rThe unreached-for cup, beaker for world-toxin,\rbreast englobing ground zero. And so we know you not.\rAnd I realize: though I have walked drenched in spring rains\rmy bare thighs have not hugged your warm bellows in a downpour.\rFor though your manic tribe is mine, the boreal chargers,\rmere rooms, a migrant’s mangy stations, have detained me.\rFor while historians of cultures hot on the spoor of roots among\rtheir root clans have heard you drum past, they looked up only briefly.\rFor though engravers assumed you would stay, given their way with your\rmusculature, accoutrements, wavy harness, tip-toe grooms,\rgear draped over your cruppers like an evening gown, its ratios\rand metalwork continuous with Genghis Khan’s and a jockey’s,\rtheir inky mastery frames cosily misleading questions:\rwhich posthouse this evening, what pasture tomorrow?\rWhereas you inquire into rupture and the unfenced: what thunder\rbetween flesh and ground, what surge from the cells even past sundown?\n	'abreast':471 'accoutr':972 'across':652,742 'aftermath':744 'aim':501 'akhilleus':410 'along':348 'also':246,435,592,788,865 'ambassador':131 'among':202,241,436,945 'antler':658 'anyon':486 'appoint':533 'arapaho':204 'arch':74 'arm':672 'ass':584,801 'assessor':841 'assum':962 'await':718 'back':175,679,691,704 'banner':120,183 'bare':903 'barouch':124 'beaker':876 'begin':623 'bellow':910 'berserk':792,795 'besid':541,851 'bit':463 'blind':773 'bloom':857 'bodi':654 'bond':498 'book':529 'boreal':922 'braid':414 'branch':332 'brazil':139 'break':284 'breast':881 'breath':113,855 'briefli':958 'bring':195 'broaden':667 'brother':248 'brows':363,599 'bubbl':745 'bulk':556 'caisson':118 'calm':850 'candl':367 'capsiz':485 'captur':451 'cascad':547 'catasroph':179 'cell':1033 'chalic':870 'chancel':41 'charger':923 'cheyenn':205 'child':105 'childbirth':590 'cinch':452 'clan':948 'clatter':155,736 'cliffsid':35 'cloud':361,612 'coat':377 'coffin':121 'cold':816,860 'colt':288 'come':49,93,102 'constel':419 'continu':992 'corkscrew':694 'cosili':1005 'crest':352 'cring':757 'crumbl':829 'crupper':983 'cuchulain':412 'cult':434 'cultur':938 'cup':809,875 'curb':787 'curri':554 'cut':806 'd':305 'dalai':697 'dancer':670 'de':645 'debouch':83 'declin':216 'deltawis':21 'demigod':481 'der':264 'detain':932 'dew':413 'dissolv':836 'downpour':913 'drape':980 'dream':87 'drench':898 'drip':715 'driver':291 'drum':214,952 'dusk':12,15 'eldest':134 'els':824 'englob':882 'engrav':961 'enter':297 'escort':686 'even':986,1011,1034 'everi':831 'everywher':68,567 'eye':31,474,483,604 'eye-spangl':603 'eyzi':650 'fade':651 'field':59 'flank':456 'flash':462,687 'flesh':1026 'flicker':345 'flow':835 'flubber':760 'flubber-flutt':759 'flutter':761 'font':644 'footloos':438 'forc':510 'foresaw':395 'forest':142,298 'foster':589 'fourteenth':696 'fourth':4 'frame':1004 'freakish':254 'fresh':418 'fuse':778 'gather':677 'gaum':646 'gear':979 'generalis