453	from Elegies, I.iv	203		\nYield prompt compliance to the maid’s desires;\rA prompt compliance fans the lover’s fires:\rGo pleas’d where’er she goes, tho’ long the way,\rTho’ the fierce Dog-star dart his sultry ray;\rTho’ painted Iris gird the bluish sky,\rAnd sure portends, that rattling storms are nigh:\rOr, if the fair one pant for sylvan fame,\rGay drag the meshes, and provoke the game:\rNay, should she choose to risk the driving gale;\rOr steer, or row, or agile hand the sail:\rNo toil, tho’ weak, tho’ fearful, thou forbear;\rNo toils should tire you, and no dangers scare:\rOccasion smiles, then snatch an ardent kiss;\rThe coy may struggle, but will grant the bliss:\rThe bliss obtain’d, the fictious struggle past,\rUnbid, they’ll clasp you in their arms at last.\r\n	'agil':87 'ardent':113 'arm':139 'bliss':123,125 'bluish':46 'choos':76 'clasp':135 'complianc':6,14 'coy':116 'd':22,127 'danger':106 'dart':37 'desir':11 'dog':35 'dog-star':34 'drag':66 'drive':80 'elegi':2 'er':24 'fair':59 'fame':64 'fan':15 'fear':96 'fictious':129 'fierc':33 'fire':19 'forbear':98 'gale':81 'game':72 'gay':65 'gird':44 'go':20 'goe':26 'grant':121 'hand':88 'i.iv':3 'iri':43 'kiss':114 'last':141 'll':134 'long':28 'lover':17 'maid':9 'may':117 'mesh':68 'nay':73 'nigh':55 'obtain':126 'occas':108 'one':60 'paint':42 'pant':61 'past':131 'plea':21 'portend':50 'prompt':5,13 'provok':70 'rattl':52 'ray':40 'risk':78 'row':85 'sail':90 'scare':107 'sky':47 'smile':109 'snatch':111 'star':36 'steer':83 'storm':53 'struggl':118,130 'sultri':39 'sure':49 'sylvan':63 'tho':27,31,41,93,95 'thou':97 'tire':102 'toil':92,100 'unbid':132 'way':30 'weak':94 'yield':4
