475	Elegies, Book One, 5	215		\nIn summer’s heat and mid-time of the day\rTo rest my limbs upon a bed I lay,\rOne window shut, the other open stood,\rWhich gave such light as twinkles in a wood,\rLike twilight glimpse at setting of the sun\rOr night being past, and yet not day begun.\rSuch light to shamefaced maidens must be shown,\rWhere they may sport, and seem to be unknown.\rThen came Corinna in a long loose gown,\rHer white neck hid with tresses hanging down:\rResembling fair Semiramis going to bed\rOr Laïs of a thousand wooers sped.\rI snatched her gown, being thin, the harm was small,\rYet strived she to be covered therewithal.\rAnd striving thus as one that would be cast,\rBetrayed herself, and yielded at the last.\rStark naked as she stood before mine eye,\rNot one wen in her body could I spy.\rWhat arms and shoulders did I touch and see,\rHow apt her breasts were to be pressed by me?\rHow smooth a belly under her waist saw I?\rHow large a leg, and what a lusty thigh?\rTo leave the rest, all liked me passing well,\rI clinged her naked body, down she fell,\rJudge you the rest: being tired she bad me kiss,\rJove send me more such afternoons as this. \r\n	'5':4 'afternoon':223 'apt':164 'arm':155 'bad':215 'bed':22,96 'begun':57 'belli':176 'betray':130 'bodi':150,204 'book':2 'breast':166 'came':76 'cast':129 'cling':201 'corinna':77 'could':151 'cover':119 'day':15,56 'elegi':1 'eye':144 'fair':92 'fell':207 'gave':33 'glimps':43 'go':94 'gown':82,107 'hang':89 'harm':111 'heat':8 'hid':86 'jove':218 'judg':208 'kiss':217 'larg':183 'last':136 'lay':24 'laï':98 'leav':192 'leg':185 'light':35,59 'like':41,196 'limb':19 'long':80 'loos':81 'lusti':189 'maiden':62 'may':68 'mid':11 'mid-tim':10 'mine':143 'must':63 'nake':138,203 'neck':85 'night':50 'one':3,25,125,146 'open':30 'pass':198 'past':52 'press':170 'resembl':91 'rest':17,194,211 'saw':180 'see':162 'seem':71 'semirami':93 'send':219 'set':45 'shamefac':61 'shoulder':157 'shown':65 'shut':27 'small