494	Once We Played	225		\nOnce we played at love together—\r   Played it smartly, if you please;\rLightly, as a windblown feather,\r   Did we stake a heart apiece.\rOh, it was delicious fooling!\r   In the hottest of the game,\rWithout thought of future cooling,\r   All too quickly burned Life’s flame.\rIn this give-and-take of glances,\r   Kisses sweet as honey dews,\rWhen we played with equal chances,\r   Did you win, or did I lose?\r\n	'apiec':26 'burn':46 'chanc':68 'cool':42 'delici':30 'dew':62 'equal':67 'feather':20 'flame':49 'fool':31 'futur':41 'game':37 'give':53 'give-and-tak':52 'glanc':57 'heart':25 'honey':61 'hottest':34 'kiss':58 'life':47 'light':16 'lose':75 'love':8 'oh':27 'play':3,6,10,65 'pleas':15 'quick':45 'smart':12 'stake':23 'sweet':59 'take':55 'thought':39 'togeth':9 'win':71 'windblown':19 'without':38
