503	The Caution	230		\nSoft kisses may be innocent;\rBut ah! too easy maid, beware;\rTho’ that is all thy kindness meant,\r’Tis love’s delusive, fatal snare.\rNo virgin e’er at first design’d\rThro’ all the maze of love to stray;\rBut each new path allures her mind,\rTill wandering on, she lose her way.\r’Tis easy ere set out to stay;\rBut who the useful art can teach,\rWhen sliding down a steepy way,\rTo stop, before the end we reach?\rKeep ever something in thy power,\rBeyond what would thy honour stain:\rHe will not dare to aim at more,\rWho for small favours sighs in vain.\r\n	'ah':9 'aim':101 'allur':47 'art':68 'bewar':13 'beyond':90 'caution':2 'd':34 'dare':99 'delus':24 'design':33 'e':29 'easi':11,58 'end':81 'er':30 'ere':59 'ever':85 'fatal':25 'favour':107 'first':32 'honour':94 'innoc':7 'keep':84 'kind':19 'kiss':4 'lose':54 'love':22,40 'maid':12 'may':5 'maze':38 'meant':20 'mind':49 'new':45 'path':46 'power':89 'reach':83 'set':60 'sigh':108 'slide':72 'small':106 'snare':26 'soft':3 'someth':86 'stain':95 'stay':63 'steepi':75 'stop':78 'stray':42 'teach':70 'thi':18,88,93 'tho':14 'thro':35 'till':50 'tis':21,57 'use':67 'vain':110 'virgin':28 'wander':51 'way':56,76 'would':92
