608	The Unquiet Grave	95		\n“The wind doth blow today, my love,      \r   And a few small drops of rain;      \rI never had but one true-love,      \r   In cold grave she was lain.      \r“I’ll do as much for my true-love\r   As any young man may;      \rI’ll sit and mourn all at her grave      \r   For a twelvemonth and a day.”\rThe twelvemonth and a day being up,      \r   The dead began to speak:        \r“Oh who sits weeping on my grave,\r   And will not let me sleep?”\r“’T is I, my love, sits on your grave,      \r   And will not let you sleep;      \rFor I crave one kiss of your clay-cold lips,\r   And that is all I seek.”\r“You crave one kiss of my clay-cold lips,      \r   But my breath smells earthy strong;      \rIf you have one kiss of my clay-cold lips,      \r   Your time will not be long.\r“’T is down in yonder garden green,      \r   Love, where we used to walk,      \rThe finest flower that e’re was seen      \r   Is withered to a stalk.      \r“The stalk is withered dry, my love,\r   So will our hearts decay;      \rSo make yourself content, my love,      \r   Till God calls you away.”\n	'away':200 'began':71 'blow':7 'breath':131 'call':198 'clay':110,126,143 'clay-cold':109,125,142 'cold':27,111,127,144 'content':193 'crave':104,120 'day':61,66 'dead':70 'decay':189 'doth':6 'dri':182 'drop':15 'e':169 'earthi':133 'finest':166 'flower':167 'garden':157 'god':197 'grave':3,28,55,80,95 'green':158 'heart':188 'kiss':106,122,139 'lain':31 'let':84,99 'lip':112,128,145 'll':33,48 'long':151 'love':10,25,41,91,159,184,195 'make':191 'man':45 'may':46 'mourn':51 'much':36 'never':19 'oh':74 'one':22,105,121,138 'rain':17 're':170 'seek':118 'seen':172 'sit':49,76,92 'sleep':86,101 'small':14 'smell':132 'speak':73 'stalk':177,179 'strong':134 'till':196 'time':147 'today':8 'true':24,40 'true-lov':23,39 'twelvemonth':58,63 'unquiet':2 'use':162 'walk':164 'weep':77 'wind':5 'wither':174,181 'yonder':156 'young':44
