611	The Song of Lewes	95		\nSitteth alle stille and herkneth to me!\r  The King of Alemaigne, by mi leaute, \rThritty thousand pound askede he \rFor to make the pees in the countre—\rAnd so he dude more.\r  Richard, thah thou be ever trichard,\r  Tricchen shalt thou nevermore.\rRichard of Alemaigne, whil that he wes king,\rHe spende all his tresour upon swiving.\rHaveth he nout of Walingford o ferling!\rLet him habbe ase he brew—bale to dring—\rMaugre Windesore.\r  Richard, thah thou be ever trichard,\r  Tricchen shalt thou nevermore.\rThe King of Alemaigne wende do full well: \rHe saised the mulne for a castel;\rWith hare sharpe swerdes he grounde the stel— \rHe wende that the sailes were mangonel\rTo helpe Windesore.\r  Richard, thah thou be ever trichard,\r  Tricchen shalt thou nevermore.\rThe king of Alemaigne gederede his host, \rMakede him a castel of a mulne post, \rWende with his prude and his muchele bost, \rBroughte from Alemaigne mony sory ghost\rTo store Windesore.\r  Richard, thah thou be ever trichard,\r  Tricchen shalt thou nevermore.\rBy God that is aboven ous, he dude muche sin\rThat lette passen over see the Erl of Warin:\rHe hath robbed Engelond, the more and the fen,\rThe gold and the selver, and iboren henne,\rFor love of Windesore. \r  Richard, thah thou be ever trichard,\r  Tricchen shalt thou nevermore.\rSire Simon de Montfort hath swore by his chin,\rHevede he now here the Erl of Warin, \rShulde he never more come to his inn,\rNe with sheld, ne with spere, ne with other gin,\rTo help of Wyndesore.\r  Richard, thah thou be ever trichard,\r  Tricchen shalt thou nevermore.\rSire Simon de Montfort hath swore by his top,\rHevede he now here Sir Hue de Bigot,\rAll he shulde equite here twelfmoneth scot—\rShulde he never more with his fot pot\rTo helpe Windesore.\r  Richard, thah thou be ever trichard,\r  Tricchen shalt thou nevermore.\rBe thee luef, be thee loth, Sire Edward,\rThou shalt ride sporeles o thy liar\rAll the righte way to Dovereward—\rShalt thou nevermore breke foreward,\rAnd that reweth sore.\rRichard, thah thou be ever trichard,\rTricchen shalt thou nevermore.\rEdward, thou dudest ase a shreward,\rForsoke thine eme’s lore.\n	'aboven':179 'alemaign':15,49,93,136,158 'all':6 'ase':72,362 'asked':22 'bale':75 'bigot':290 'bost':155 'breke':343 'brew':74 'brought':156 'castel':104,143 'chin':233 'come':246 'countr':31 'de':227,276,289 'dovereward':339 'dring':77 'dude':35,182 'dudest':361 'edward':326,359 'eme':367 'engelond':197 'equit':294 'erl':191,239 'ever':41,84,127,169,219,268,313,353 'fen':202 'ferl':68 'foreward':344 'forsok':365 'fot':304 'full':96 'gedered':137 'ghost':161 'gin':259 'god':176 'gold':204 'ground':110 'habb':71 'hare':106 'hath':195,229,278 'haveth':62 'help':121,261,307 'henn':210 'herkneth':9 'heved':234,283 'host':139 'hue':288 'iboren':209 'inn':249 'king':13,54,91,134 'leaut':18 'let':69 'lett':186 'lew':4 'liar':333 'lore':369 'loth':324 'love':212 'luef':321 'make':26 'maked':140 'mangonel':119 'maugr':78 'mi':17 'moni':159 'montfort':228,277 'much':183 'muchel':154 'muln':101,146 'ne':250,253,256 'never':244,300 'nevermor':46,89,132,174,224,273,318,342,358 'nout':64 'o':67,331 'ous':180 'passen':187 'pee':28 'post':147 'pot':305 'pound':21 'prude':151 'reweth':347 'richard':37,47,80,123,165,215,264,309,349 'ride':329 'right':336 'rob':196 'sail':117 'sais':99 'scot':297 'see':189 'selver':207 'shalt':44,87,130,172,222,271,316,328,340,356 'sharp':107 'sheld':252 'shreward':364 'shuld':242,293,298 'simon':226,275 'sin':184 'sir':287 'sire':225,274,325 'sitteth':5 'song':2 'sore':348 'sori':160 'spend':56 'spere':255 'sporel':330 'stel':112 'still':7 'store':163 'swerd':108 'swive':61 'swore':230,279 'thah':38,81,124,166,216,265,310,350 'thee':320,323 'thi':332 'thine':366 'thou':39,45,82,88,125,131,167,173,217,223,266,272,311,317,327,341,351,357,360 'thousand':20 'thritti':19 'top':282 'tresour':59 'tricchen':43,86,129,171,221,270,315,355 'trichard':42,85,128,170,22