613	Jesus Comforts His Mother	95		\nA baby is borne us blis to bring;\rA maidden, I hard, “Loullay,” sing: \r“Dere son, now leive thy wepping,\rThy fadere is the King of Blis.”\r“Nay! Dere modere, for you weppe I noght,\rBut for thinges that shall be wroght,\rOr that I have mankind iboght.\rWas ther never pain like it, iwis.”\r“Pes! dere sone, say thou me not so.\rThou art my child, I have no mo.\rAlas! That I shuld see this wo:\rIt were to me gret heivynis.”\r“My hondes, modere, that ye now see,\rThay shall be nailed one a tree;\rMy feit, also, fastned shall be: \rFull mony shall wepe that it shall see.”\r“Alas! dere son, sorrow now is my happe\rTo see my child that soukes my pappe\rSo ruthfully taken out of my lappe.\rIt were to me gret heivynis.”\r“Also, modere, ther shall a speire\rMy tendere hert all to-teire:\rThe blud shall kevere my body there.\rGret ruthe it shall be to see.”\r“A! dere sone, that is a heivy cas.\rWhen Gabrell knelled before my face\rAnd said, ‘Heille! Lady, full of grace,’\rHe never told me nothing of this.\r“Dere modere, pes!  Nowe I you pray,\rAnd take no sorrow for that I say, \rBut singe this song, ‘By, by, loullay,’\rTo drive away all heivynis.”\n	'ala':76,117 'also':105,146 'art':69 'away':225 'babi':6 'blis':10,31 'blud':160 'bodi':164 'born':8 'bring':12 'cas':180 'child':71,128 'comfort':2 'dere':19,33,61,118,174,201 'drive':224 'face':186 'fader':26 'fastn':106 'feit':104 'full':109,191 'gabrel':182 'grace':193 'gret':87,144,166 'happ':124 'hard':16 'heill':189 'heivi':179 'heivyni':88,145,227 'hert':154 'hond':90 'iboght':52 'iwi':59 'jesus':1 'kever':162 'king':29 'knell':183 'ladi':190 'lapp':139 'leiv':22 'like':57 'loullay':17,222 'maidden':14 'mankind':51 'mo':75 'moder':34,91,147,202 'moni':110 'mother':4 'nail':99 'nay':32 'never':55,195 'noght':39 'noth':198 'now':204 'one':100 'pain':56 'papp':132 'pes':60,203 'pray':207 'ruth':134,167 'said':188 'say':63,215 'see':80,95,116,126,172 'shall':44,97,107,111,115,149,161,169 