675	from To Priapus: Elegies 1.iv	203		\nFar from the tender Tribe of Boys remove,\rFor they’ve a thousand ways to kindle Love.\rThis, pleases as he strides the manag’d Horse,\rAnd holds the taughten’d Rein with early Force;\rThis, as he swims, delights thy Fancy best,\rRaising the smiling Wave with snowy Breast:\rThis, with a comely Look and manly Airs;\rAnd that with Virgin Modesty ensnares.\rBut if at first you find him not inclin’d\rTo Love, have Patience, Time will change his Mind.\r                    *\r      And you, what’er your Fav’rite does, approve,\rFor Condescension leads the Way to love.\rGo with him where he goes, tho’ long the Way,\rAnd the fierce Dog-star fires the sultry Day;\rOr the gay Rainbow girds the bluish Sky,\rAnd threatens rattling Show’rs of Rain are nigh.\rIf sailing on the Water by his Will,\rThen steer the Wherry with a dext’rous Skill:\rNor think it hard Fatigues and Pains to bear,\rBut still be ready with a willing Cheer.\rIf he’ll inclose the Vales for savage Spoils,\rThen on thy Shoulders bear the Nets and Toils;\rIf Fencing be the Fav’rite Sport he’ll use, \rTake up the Files, and artlessly oppose;\rSeem as intent, yet oft expose your Breast,\rNeglect your Guard, and let him get the best;\rThen he’ll be mild, then you a Kiss may seize,\rHe’ll struggle, but at length comply with ease;\rReluctant, tho’ at first you’ll find him grow\rEv’n fond, when round your Neck his Arms he’ll throw. \r\n	'1.iv':5 'air':63 'approv':97 'arm':265 'artless':209 'bear':167,189 'best':48,227 'bluish':131 'boy':12 'breast':55,218 'chang':86 'cheer':175 'come':59 'compli':245 'condescens':99 'd':30,36,79 'day':124 'delight':45 'dext':156 'dog':119 'dog-star':118 'earli':39 'eas':247 'elegi':4 'ensnar':69 'er':92 'ev':257 'expos':216 'fanci':47 'far':6 'fatigu':163 'fav':94,198 'fenc':195 'fierc':117 'file':207 'find':75,254 'fire':121 'first':73,251 'fond':259 'forc':40 'gay':127 'get':225 'gird':129 'go':105 'goe':110 'grow':256 'guard':221 'hard':162 