819	The Strength of Fields	311		\nMoth-force a small town always has,             Given the night.                                                 What field-forms can be,          Outlying the small civic light-decisions over                A man walking near home?                                                                          Men are not where he is         Exactly now, but they are around him    around him like the strength Of fields.    The solar system floats on     Above him in town-moths.                                                          Tell me, train-sound,     With all your long-lost grief,                                                          what I can give.       Dear Lord of all the fields                                                          what am I going to do?                                         Street-lights, blue-force and frail As the homes of men, tell me how to do it    how     To withdraw    how to penetrate and find the source         Of the power you always had                                                             light as a moth, and rising        With the level and moonlit expansion     Of the fields around, and the sleep of hoping men.        You?    I?    What difference is there?    We can all be saved        By a secret blooming. Now as I walk The night    and you walk with me    we know simplicity      Is close to the source that sleeping men        Search for in their home-deep beds.        We know that the sun is away    we know that the sun can be conquered      By moths, in blue home-town air.           The stars splinter, pointed and wild. The dead lie under The pastures.    They look on and help.    Tell me, freight-train,                             When there is no one else    To hear. Tell me in a voice the sea          Would have, if it had not a better one: as it lifts,           Hundreds of miles away, its fumbling, deep-structured roar                Like the profound, unstoppable craving             Of nations for their wish.                                                                     Hunger, time and the moon:          The moon lying on the brain                                                                     as on the excited sea    as on           The strength of fields. Lord, let me shake            With purpose.    Wild hope can always spring            From tended strength.    Everything is in that.             That and nothing but kindness.    More kindness, dear Lord Of the renewing green.    That is where it all has to start:          With the simplest things. More kindness will do nothing less              Than save every sleeping one              And night-walking one          Of us.                          My life belongs to the world. I will do what I can.\n	'air':218 'alway':11,127,319 'around':46,48,144 'away':202,271 'bed':195 'belong':373 'better':263 'bloom':165 'blue':98,214 'blue-forc':97 'brain':298 'civic':25 'close':181 'conquer':210 'crave':282 'dead':226 'dear':82,335 'decis':28 'deep':194,275 'deep-structur':274 'differ':154 'els':246 'everi':361 'everyth':324 'exact':41 'excit':302 'expans':140 'field':4,18,54,87,143,309 'field-form':17 'find':120 'float':58 'forc':7,99 'form':19 'frail':101 'freight':239 'freight-train':238 'fumbl':273 'give':81 'given':13 'go':91 'green':340 'grief':77 'hear':248 'help':235 'home':34,104,193,216 'home-deep':192 'home-town':215 'hope':149,317 'hundr':268 'hunger':288 'kind':332,334,354 'know':178,197,204 'less':358 'let':311 'level':137 'lie':227,295 'life':372 'lift':267 'light':27,96,129 'light-decis':26 'like':50,278 'long':75 'long-lost':74 'look':232 'lord':83,310,336 'lost':76 'man':31 'men':35,106,150,187 'mile':270 'moon':292,294 'moonlit':139 'moth':6,65,132,212 'moth-forc':5 'nation':284 'near':33 'night':15,171,366 'night-walk':365 'noth':330,357 'one':245,264,363,368 'out':22 'pastur':230 'penetr':118 'point':222 'power':125 'profound':280 'purpos':315 'renew':3