828	For My Contemporaries	310		\nHow time reverses  The proud in heart!  I now make verses  Who aimed at art. But I sleep well.  Ambitious boys Whose big lines swell  With spiritual noise, Despise me not! And be not queasy  To praise somewhat:  Verse is not easy. But rage who will. Time that procured me  Good sense and skill  Of madness cured me.\n	'aim':16 'ambiti':23 'art':18 'big':26 'boy':24 'contemporari':3 'cure':60 'despis':32 'easi':45 'good':54 'heart':10 'line':27 'mad':59 'make':13 'nois':31 'prais':40 'procur':52 'proud':8 'queasi':38 'rage':47 'revers':6 'sens':55 'skill':57 'sleep':21 'somewhat':41 'spiritu':30 'swell':28 'time':5,50 'vers':14,42 'well':22 'whose':25
829	Meditation on Statistical Method	310		\nPlato, despair! We prove by norms How numbers bear Empiric forms, How random wrong Will average right If time be long And error slight, But in our hearts Hyperbole Curves and departs To infinity. Error is boundless. Nor hope nor doubt, Though both be groundless, Will average out.\n	'averag':20,51 'bear':13 'boundless':41 'curv':34 'depart':36 'despair':6 'doubt':45 'empir':14 'error':27,39 'form':15 'groundless':49 'heart':32 'hope':43 'hyperbol':33 'infin':38 'long':25 'medit':1 'method':4 'norm':10 'number':12 'plato':5 'prove':8 'random':17 'right':21 'slight':28 'statist':3 'though':46 'time':23 'wrong':18
831	Montana Pastoral	310		\nI am no shepherd of a child’s surmises. I have seen fear where the coiled serpent rises, Thirst where the grasses burn in early May And thistle, mustard, and the wild oat stay. There is dust in this air. I saw in the heat Grasshoppers busy in the threshing wheat. So to this hour. Through the warm dusk I drove To blizzards sifting on the hissing stove, And found no images of pastoral will, But fear, thirst, hunger, and this huddled chill.\n	'air':42 'blizzard':65 'burn':25 'busi':49 'child':9 'chill':85 'coil':18 'drove':63 'dusk':61 'dust':39 'earli':27 'fear':15,79 'found':72 'grass':24 'grasshopp':48 'heat':47 'hiss':69 'hour':57 'huddl':84 'hunger':81 'imag':74 'may':28 'montana':1 'mustard':31 'oat':35 'pastor':2,76 'rise':20 'saw':44 'seen':14 'serpent':19 'shepherd':6 'sift':66 'stay':36 'stove':70 'surmis':11 'thirst':21,80 'thistl':30 'thresh':52 'warm':60 'wheat':53 'wild':34
