840	Benjamin Banneker Helps to Build a City	312		\nIn a morning coat,\rhands locked behind your back,\ryou walk gravely along the lines in your head.\rThese others stand with you, \rsquinting the city into place, \ryet cannot see what you see, \rwhat you would see\ra vision of these paths, \rlaid out like a star,\ror like a body,\rthe seed vibrating within itself, \rbreaking into the open,\rdancing up to stop at the end of the universe.\rI say your vision goes as far as this, \rthe egg of the world,\rwhere everything remains, and moves,\rholding what is most against it against itself,\rmoving, as though it knew its end, against death.\rIn that order,\rthe smallest life, the small event take shape.\rYes, even here at this point, \rAmma's plan consumes you,\rthe prefigured man, Nommo, the son of God.\rI call you into this time,\rback to that spot\rand read these prefigurations \rinto your mind,\rand know it could not be strange to you \rto stand in the dark and emptiness \rof a city not your vision alone.\rNow, I have searched the texts\rand forms of cities that burned,\rthat decayed, or gave their children away, \rhave been picking at my skin,\rwatching my hand move,\rfeeling the weight and shuttle of my body, \rlistening with an ear as large as God's \rto catch some familiar tone in my voice. \rNow, I am here in your city,\rtrying to find that spot\rwhere the vibration starts.\rThere must be some mistake.\rOver the earth, \rin an open space,\ryou and I step to the time\rof another ceremony. \rThese people, changed,\rbut still ours,\rshake another myth \rfrom that egg.\rSome will tell you\rthat beginnings are only\rpossible here,\rthat only the clamor of these drums\rcould bring our God to earth.\rA city, like a life,\rmust be made in purity.\rSo they call you,\rknowing you are intimate with stars,\rto create this city, this body.\rSo they call you,\rknowing you must purge the ground.\r“Sir, suffer me to recall to your mind that time, in which the arms and tyranny of the British crown were exerted, with every powerful effort in order to reduce you to a state of servitude: look back, I entreat you, on the variety of dangers to which you were exposed; reflect on that time, in which every human aid appeared unavailable, and in which even hope and fortitude wore the aspect of inability to the conflict, and you cannot but be led to a serious and grateful sense of your miraculous and providential preservation; you cannot but acknowledge, that the present freedom and tranquility which you enjoy you have mercifully received, and that it is the peculiar blessing of Heaven.”\r	'acknowledg':446 'aid':407 'alon':184 'along':20 'amma':132 'anoth':275,284 'appear':408 'arm':361 'aspect':419 'away':203 'back':16,151,385 'bannek':2 'begin':294 'behind':14 'benjamin':1 'bless':466 'bodi':59,221,337 'break':65 'bring':307 'british':366 'build':5 'burn':196 'call':146,324,340 'cannot':37,427,444 'catch':232 'ceremoni':276 'chang':279 'children':202 'citi':7,33,180,194,245,313,335 'clamor':302 'coat':11 'conflict':424 'consum':135 'could':165,306 'creat':333 'crown':367 'danc':69 'danger':393 'dark':175 'death':114 'decay':198 'drum':305 'ear':225 'earth':262,311 'effort':373 'egg':89,288 'empti':177 'end':75,112 'enjoy':455 'entreat':387 'even':127,413 'event':123 'everi':371,405 'everyth':94 'exert':369 'expos':398 'familiar':234 'far':85 'feel':214 'find':248 'form':192 'fortitud':416 'freedom':450 'gave':200 'god':144,229,309 'goe':83 'grate':435 'grave':19 'ground':347 'hand':12,212 'head':25 'heaven':468 'help':3 'hold':98 'hope':414 'human':406 'inabl':421 'intim':329 'knew':110 'know':163,326,342 'laid':51 'larg':227 'led':430 'life':120,316 'like':53,57,314 'line':22 'listen':222 'lock':13 'look':384 'made':319 'man':139 'merci':458 'mind':161,355 'miracul':439 'mistak':259 'morn':10 'move':97,106,213 'must':256,317,344 'myth':285 'nommo':140 'open':68,265 'order':117,375 'other':27 'path':50 'peculiar':465 'peopl':278 'pick':206 'place'