844	The Healing Improvisation of Hair	312		\nIf you undo your do you would be strange. Hair has been on my mind.  I used to lean in the doorway and watch my stony woman wind the copper through the black, and play with my understanding, show me she cóuld  take a cup of river water, and watch it shimmy, watch it change, turn around and become ash bone.  Wind in the cottonwoods wakes me  to a day so thin its breastbone  shows, so paid out it shakes me free  of its blue dust. I will arrange  that river water, bottom juice.  I conjure my head in the stream  and ride with the silk feel of it as my woman bathes me, and shaves  away the scorn, sponges the grit  of solitude from my skin, laves  the salt water of self-esteem  over my feathering body. How like joy to come upon me  in remembering a head of hair  and the way water would caress  it, and stress beauty in the flair  and cut of the only witness to my dance under sorrow's tree. This swift darkness is spring's first hour. I carried my life, like a stone,  in a ragged pocket, but I had a true weaving song, a sly  way with rhythm, a healing tone.\n	'around':62 'arrang':94 'ash':65 'away':122 'bath':118 'beauti':167 'becom':64 'black':38 'blue':90 'bodi':144 'bone':66 'bottom':98 'breastbon':79 'caress':163 'carri':193 'chang':60 'come':149 'conjur':101 'copper':35 'cottonwood':70 'cup':50 'cut':172 'cóuld':47 'danc':179 'dark':186 'day':75 'doorway':27 'dust':91 'esteem':140 'feather':143 'feel':112 'first':190 'flair':170 'free':87 'grit':127 'hair':5,15,157 'head':103,155 'heal':2,216 'hour':191 'improvis':3 'joy':147 'juic':99 'lave':133 'lean':24 'life':195 'like':146,196 'mind':20 'paid':82 'play':40 'pocket':202 'rag':201 'rememb':153 'rhythm':214 'ride':108 'river':52,96 'salt':135 'scorn':124 'self':139 'self-esteem':138 'shake':85 'shave':121 'shimmi':57 'show':44,80 'silk':111 'skin':132 'sli':211 'solitud':129 'song':209 'sorrow':181 'spong':125 'spring':188 'stone':198 'stoni':31 'strang':14 'stream':106 'st