873	Sunday:  New Guinea	314		\nThe bugle sounds the measured call to prayers, \r   The band starts bravely with a clarion hymn, \r   From every side, singly, in groups, in pairs,\rEach to his kind of service comes to worship Him.\r   Our faces washed, our hearts in the right place, \r   We kneel or stand or listen from our tents; \r   Half-naked natives with their kind of grace\rMove down the road with balanced staffs like mendicants.\r   And over the hill the guns bang like a door \r   And planes repeat their mission in the heights. \r   The jungle outmaneuvers creeping war\rAnd crawls within the circle of our sacred rites.\r   I long for our disheveled Sundays home, \r   Breakfast, the comics, news of latest crimes, \r   Talk without reference, and palindromes,\rSleep and the Philharmonic and the ponderous Times.\r   I long for lounging in the afternoons\r   Of clean intelligent warmth, my brother’s mind, \r   Books and thin plates and flowers and shining spoons,\rAnd your love’s presence, snowy, beautiful, and kind.\n	'afternoon':139 'balanc':70 'band':13 'bang':80 'beauti':163 'book':148 'brave':15 'breakfast':113 'brother':145 'bugl':5 'call':9 'circl':101 'clarion':18 'clean':141 'come':34 'comic':115 'crawl':98 'creep':95 'crime':119 'dishevel':110 'door':83 'everi':21 'face':39 'flower':153 'grace':64 'group':25 'guinea':3 'gun':79 'half':57 'half-nak':56 'heart':42 'height':91 'hill':77 'home':112 'hymn':19 'intellig':142 'jungl':93 'kind':31,62,165 'kneel':48 'latest':118 'like':72,81 'listen':52 'long':107,134 'loung':136 'love':159 'measur':8 'mendic':73 'mind':147 'mission':88 'move':65 'nake':58 'nativ':59 'new':2 'news':116 'outmaneuv':94 'pair':27 'palindrom':124 'philharmon':128 'place':46 'plane':85 'plate':151 'ponder':131 'prayer':11 'presenc':161 'refer':122 'repeat':86 'right':45 'rite':105 'road':68 'sacr':104 'servic':33 'shine':155 'side':22 'singl':23 'sleep':125 'snowi':162 'sound':6 'spoon':156 'staff':71 'stand':50 'start':14 'sunday':1,