867	The Intellectual	314		\nThe man behind the book may not be man, \rHis own man or the book’s or yet the time’s, \rBut still be whole, deciding what he can \rIn praise of politics or German rimes;\rBut the intellectual lights a cigarette\rAnd offers it lit to the lady, whose odd smile \rIs the merest hyphenlest he should forget \rWhat he has been resuming all the while.\rHe talks to overhear, she to withdraw\rTo some interior feminine fireside\rWhere the back arches, beauty puts forth a paw \rLike a black puma stretching in velvet pride,\rMaking him think of cats, a stray of which \rSome days sets up a howling in his brain, \rPure interference such as this neat bitch \rSeems to create from listening disdain.\rBut talk is all the value, the release,\rTalk is the very fillip of an act,\rThe frame and subject of the masterpiece \rUnder whose film of age the face is cracked.\rHis own forehead glows like expensive wood, \rBut back of it the mind is disengaged,\rSelf-sealing clock recording bad and good \rAt constant temperature, intact, unaged.\rBut strange, his body is an open house \rInviting every passerby to stay;\rThe city to and fro beneath his brows\rWanders and drinks and chats from night to day.\rThink of a private thought, indecent room \rWhere one might kiss his daughter before bed! \rLife is embarrassed; shut the family tomb, \rConsole your neighbor for his recent dead;\rDo something! die in Spain or paint a green \rGouache, go into business (Rimbaud did), \rOr start another Little Magazine,\rOr move in with a woman, have a kid.\rInvulnerable, impossible, immune,\rDo what you will, your will will not be done \rBut dissipate the light of afternoon\rTill evening flickers like the midnight sun,\rAnd midnight shouts and dies: I’d rather be \rA milkman walking in his sleep at dawn \rBearing fat quarts of cream, and so be free, \rCrossing alone and cold from lawn to lawn.\rI’d rather be a barber and cut hair\rThan walk with you in gilt museum halls, \rYou and the puma-lady, she so rare \rExhaling her silk soul upon the walls.\rGo take yourselves apart, but let me be \rThe fault you find with everyman. I spit, \rI laugh, I fight; and you, l’homme qui rît;\rSwallow your stale saliva, and still sit.\r\n	'act':146 'afternoon':297 'age':158 'alon':332 'anoth':267 'apart':375 'arch':86 'back':85,171 'bad':183 'barber':344 'bear':322 'beauti':87 'bed':235 'behind':5 'beneath':209 'bitch':124 'black':94 'bodi':194 'book':7,17 'brain':117 'brow':211 'busi':262 'cat':104 'chat':216 'cigarett':44 'citi':205 'clock':181 'cold':334 'consol':243 'constant':187 'crack':162 'cream':326 'creat':127 'cross':331 'cut':346 'd':311,340 'daughter':233 'dawn':321 'day':110,220 'dead':249 'decid':28 'die':252,309 'disdain':130 'disengag':177 'dissip':293 'done':291 'drink':214 'embarrass':238 'even':299 'everi':200 'everyman':385 'exhal':365 'expens':168 'face':160 'famili':241 'fat':323 'fault':381 'feminin':81 'fight':391 'fillip':143 'film':156 'find':383 'firesid':82 'flicker':300 'forehead':165 'forget':62 'forth':89 'frame':148 'free':330 'fro':208 'german':37 'gilt':353 'glow':166 'go':260,372 'good':185 'gouach':259 'green':258 'hair':347 'hall':355 'homm':395 'hous':198 'howl':114 'hyphen':58 'immun':281 'imposs':280 'indec':226 'intact':189 'intellectu':2,41 'interfer':119 'interior':80 'invit':199 'invulner':279 'kid':278 'kiss':231 'l':394 'ladi':51,361 'laugh':389 'lawn':336,338 'lest':59 'let':377 'life':236 'light':42,295 'like':92,167,301 'listen':129 'lit':48 'littl':268 'magazin':269 'make':100 'man':4,11,14 'masterpiec':153 'may':8 'merest':57 'midnight':303,306 'might':230 'milkman':315 'mind':175 'move':271 'museum':354 'neat':123 'neighbor':245 'night':218 'odd':53 'offer':46 'one':229 'open':197 'overhear':74 'paint':256 'passerbi':201 'paw':91 'polit':35 'prais':33 'pride':99 'privat':224 'puma':95,360 'puma-ladi':359 'pure':118 'put':88 'quart':324 'qui':396 'rare':364 'rather':312,341 'recent':248 'record':182 'releas':1