870	Imps	315		\nFire isn’t allowed, for the sake of the books.\rThe lean monk-copyist who scribes the books is slate-blue at his fingertips\rthis steely late-November day in the year 1000. Brother Ambrosio \rhuffs some perfunctory warmth on his stiffening hands, \rthen bends again to his goat’s-horn of ink. For every line, \rhe believes, he’s forgiven a sin. And now he’s at his heavy \runcial letters, and will be for nine hours more,\runtil a slab of bread and a beet relieve his transcriptual ardor. \rWhat he copies?—psalter, missal, hagiography:\rthe predetermined and sanctioned community passions \rof a religious culture. Nothing like the twentieth century’s \rprevalent kneejerk “self-expression.” Nothing like the priest,\rexcuse me: former priest, and former nun, on daytime talk TV, \rwho live, she tells us, in a “trinity of love” with the former \rcreator-of-tourist-ashtrays-out-of-catfish-heads. This is, \rshe insists, the final and jubilant stage of a lifelong “quest \rto feel belongingness” initiated thirty years before \rby parents skittering cross-country with the military: they were wholly rootless, and so she grew up “unable to commit.” The following day, \ra man confesses to pedophilia because of a lesbian aunt. \rA woman says she robbed the Sack-N-Save of $13.42 \r“because of what they’re dumping in the water supply, it makes me \rgo all freaky.” Steve was bounced out from The Chicken Shack \r“because I’m Scandinavian.” The culture\rof blame is so completely exterior in its search for cause, \rsome days I wake to think I’ll find most people laboring\runder the weight of sci-fi-style mind parasites, like fleshy turbans \rspewing in, and feeding off, their brain blood. This (by “this”\rI mean of course a recognition of the magic of objective correlative \rboppin’ about in the spotlight) is, to some length, \runderstandable: you can’t beat the miniscule carry-along \rconvenience of a silicon chip invisibly set in something, \rBUT for sheer persuasive visual power, that can’t touch \ra 1940s generating plant, its giant Alcatrazian shape \ragainst the sky, and the enormous wrestling electrical crackles \rsnaking its rooftop pylon. In the scriptorium, even\r—such an isolated unit of human endeavor, its limited range \rof reactions surely is pure—when Brother Ambrosio \rnods off, sleepy in his long day’s long eighth hour \rof thickly nibbed and careful letters, he knows\rit’s imps in league with Satan that keep pulling down his eyelids. \rIf in scratching his flea-measled thigh he spills \ra hand’s-expanse of ink across the vellum page, the fleas \rare tiny devils on a guerilla mission from Hell. \rAnd once a devilkin took lodging in his belly, and there \rcreated “rumbling noises like a toad, and which, for hours, \rspoiled the concentration of all of the other Brothers.” \rWe find parchment scraps with appropriate exorcisms:\r“Away! you flaming sow, you poisoned udder,\ryou arse of the arch-fiend, shit-fly, stinking he-goat, \rout out out, away, back into thine infernal kitchen,\ryou bestial puke!” We also find\rthose charming marginal doodles (sprigs in flower, \runicorns, seemingly every songbird in Creation): such \rdiminutive external bodies given to the longings of these \rcooped-up men. And when they came to drag my friend Jess \rscreaming to the ward, because he was beating his head \ron the lawyer’s steps, it was clear to us all that the chemicals \rin his mind had turned against him. It was clear to Jess\rthat he was being hunted like prey by hounds from the moon.\r\n	'1000':37 '13.42':226 '1940s':355 'across':446 'alcatrazian':360 'allow':5 'along':334 'also':532 'ambrosio':39,396 'appropri':496 'arch':510 'arch-fiend':509 'ardor':96 'ars':506 'ashtray':156 'aunt':214 'away':498,522 'back':523 'beat':329,577 'beet':92 'believ':63 'belli':469 'belonging':176 'bend':49 'bestial':529 'blame':258 'blood':300 'blue':24 'bodi':550 'book':11,20 'boppin':316 'bounc':245 'brain':299 'bread':89 'brother':38,395,490 'ca