875	Buick	314		\nAs a sloop with a sweep of immaculate wing on her delicate spine\rAnd a keel as steel as a root that holds in the sea as she leans,\rLeaning and laughing, my warm-hearted beauty, you ride, you ride,\rYou tack on the curves with parabola speed and a kiss of goodbye,\rLike a thoroughbred sloop, my new high-spirited spirit, my kiss.\rAs my foot suggests that you leap in the air with your hips of a girl,\rMy finger that praises your wheel and announces your voices of song,\rFlouncing your skirts, you blueness of joy, you flirt of politeness,\rYou leap, you intelligence, essence of wheelness with silvery nose,\rAnd your platinum clocks of excitement stir like the hairs of a fern.\rBut how alien you are from the booming belts of your birth and the smoke\rWhere you turned on the stinging lathes of Detroit and Lansing at night\rAnd shrieked at the torch in your secret parts and the amorous tests,\rBut now with your eyes that enter the future of roads you forget;\rYou are all instinct with your phosphorous glow and your streaking hair.\rAnd now when we stop it is not as the bird from the shell that I leave\rOr the leathery pilot who steps from his bird with a sneer of delight,\rAnd not as the ignorant beast do you squat and watch me depart,\rBut with exquisite breathing you smile, with satisfaction of love,\rAnd I touch you again as you tick in the silence and settle in sleep.\n	'air':77 'alien':132 'amor':169 'announc':91 'beast':232 'beauti':38 'belt':138 'bird':206,221 'birth':141 'blueness':100 'boom':137 'breath':243 'buick':1 'clock':120 'curv':47 'delic':13 'delight':226 'depart':239 'detroit':153 'enter':177 'essenc':111 'excit':122 'exquisit':242 'eye':175 'fern':129 'finger':85 'flirt':104 'flounc':96 'foot':70 'forget':183 'futur':179 'girl':83 'glow':191 'goodby':55 'hair':126,195 'heart':37 'high':63 'high-spirit':62 'hip':80 'hold':24 'ignor':231 'immacul':9 'instinct':187 'intellig':110 'joy':102 'keel':17 'kiss':53,67 'lans':155 'lath':151 'l