876	Stonehenge	315		\nEach morning he’d anoint the room’s four corners \rwith an arc of piss, and then—until \rhe was forcibly halted—beat his forehead open\ron the eastern wall, the “sunrise wall,” \rincanting a doggerel prayer about God\rthe Flower, God of the Hot Plucked Heart; and\rshe, if loose in the halls, would join him,\rsquatting in the center of the room and masturbating \rwith a stolen bar of soap. This isn’t why they were sent to the madhouse: this is what \rthey needed to do once in the madhouse: this \ris the only meaningful ritual they could fashion \rthere, created from the few, make-do \rmaterials available. It isn’t wondrous strange \rmore than the mega-boozhwah formulaic splendor \rof my sister’s wedding ten, eleven years ago: \rher opulent bouquet of plastic flowers \r(for the wilting pour of wattage at the photo session), \rnigglingly arranged to match the real bouquet \rshe carried down the aisle, bloom per bloom; \rthe five-foot Taj Mahal of sculpted pastel sherbet; \rendless “Fiddler on the Roof”; I’m sorry \rnow I cranked my academic sneer hauteur in place \rall night. I’m sorry I didn’t lose myself \rlike a drunken bee in a room-sized rose, \rin waltzing Auntie Sally to the lush swell \rof the band. We need this thing. There’s not one \rmineral in Stonehenge that our blood can’t also raise. \rOne dusk, one vividly contusion-color \rdusk, with my fists in my pockets and \ra puzzle of fish-rib clouds in the sky, I \rstopped at the low-level glow of a basement window \r(Hot Good Noodle Shop) and furtively looked in:\ra full-grown pig was splayed on the table,\rstunned but fitfully twitching, it looked as if\rit had grasshoppers under its skin. A man and a woman \rslit that body jaw-to-ass with an ornate knife, \rand then they both scooped out a tumble \rof many dozens of wasps, preserved\rby the oils of living pig to a beautiful black and amber \rgem-like sheen. I saw it. Did I\rsee it? From inside this, over their wrists \rin the tripes, they carefully removed\rthe wooden doll of a man and the wooden doll of a woman \rmaybe two inches tall, a tiny lacquered sun \rand matching brass coin of a moon, and then \ra child’s-third-grade-version of a house \rmade out of pallid wax: a square of walls, \ra pyramid roof, and a real smoking chimney.\r\n	'academ':189 'ago':135 'aisl':163 'also':241 'amber':353 'anoint':6 'arc':14 'arrang':153 'ass':323 'aunti':216 'avail':113 'band':224 'bar':71 'basement':278 'beat':24 'beauti':350 'bee':207 'black':351 'blood':238 'bloom':164,166 'bodi':319 'boozhwah':124 'bouquet':138,158 'brass':400 'care':375 'carri':160 'center':62 'child':408 'chimney':433 'cloud':264 'coin':401 'color':249 'contus':248 'contusion-color':247 'corner':11 'could':102 'crank':187 'creat':105 'd':5 'didn':200 'doggerel':37 'doll':379,386 'dozen':338 'drunken':206 'dusk':244,250 'eastern':30 'eleven':133 'endless':177 'fashion':103 'fiddler':178 'fish':262 'fish-rib':261 'fist':253 'fit':300 'five':169 'five-foot':168 'flower':42,141 'foot':170 'forcibl':22 'forehead':26 'formula':125 'four':10 'full':290 'full-grown':289 'furtiv':285 'gem':355 'gem-lik':354 'glow':275 'god':40,43 'good':281 'grade':412 'grasshopp':308 'grown':291 'hall':55 'halt':23 'hauteur':191 'heart':48 'hot':46,280 'hous':416 'incant':35 'inch':392 'insid':366 'isn':75,115 'jaw':321 'jaw-to-ass':320 'join':57 'knife':327 'lacquer':396 'level':274 'like':204,356 'live':346 'look':286,303 'loos':52 'lose':202 'low':273 'low-level':272 'lush':220 'm':183,197 'made':417 'madhous':83,94 'mahal':172 'make':110 'make-do':109 'man':313,382 'mani':337 'masturb':67 'match':155,399 'materi':112 'mayb':390 'meaning':99 'mega':123 'mega-boozhwah':122 'miner':233 'moon':404 'morn':3 'need':88,226 'niggl':152 'night':195 'noodl':282 'oil':344 'one':232,243,245 'open':27 'opul':137 'ornat':326 'pallid':420 'pastel':175 'per':165 'photo':150 'pig':292,347 'piss':16 'place':193 'plastic':140 'pluck':47 'pocket':256 'pour':145 'prayer':38 'pr