989	The Foggy, Foggy Blue	326		\nWhen I was a young man, I loved to write poems            And I called a spade a spade And the only only thing that made me sing            Was to lift the masks at the masquerade.   I took them off my own face,          I took them off others too And the only only wrong in all my song          Was the view that I knew what was true. Now I am older and tireder too          And the tasks with the masks are quite trying.   I’d gladly gladly stop if I only only knew          A better way to keep from lying,   And not get nervous and blue          When I said something quite untrue:   I looked all around and all over          To find something else to do:   I tried to be less romantic          I tried to be less starry-eyed too:   But I only got mixed up and frantic          Forgetting what was false and what was true. But tonight I am going to the masked ball,          Because it has occurred to me That the masks are more true than the faces:          —Perhaps this too is poetry? I no longer yearn to be naïve and stern          And masked balls fascinate me: Now that I know that most falsehoods are true          Perhaps I can join the charade?   This is, at any rate, my new and true view:          Let live and believe, I say. The only only thing is to believe in everything:          It’s more fun and safer that way!\n	'around':119 'ball':168,200 'believ':231,240 'better':98 'blue':4,109 'call':18 'charad':217 'd':88 'els':126 'everyth':242 'eye':142 'face':46,183 'fals':155 'falsehood':209 'fascin':201 'find':124 'foggi':2,3 'forget':152 'frantic':151 'fun':246 'get':106 'glad':89,90 'go':164 'got':147 'join':215 'keep':101 'knew':67,96 'know':206 'less':133,139 'let':228 'lie':103 'lift':34 'live':229 'longer':191 'look':117 'love':12 'made':29 'man':10 'mask':36,83,167,177,199 'masquerad':39 'mix':148 'naïv':195 'nervous':107 'new':224 'occur':172 'older':74 'other':51 'perhap':184,212 'poem':15 'poetri':188 'quit':85,114 'rate':222 '